description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits neuromuscular transmission by blocking acetylcholine release from the nerve termini. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that acts in vivo as an anti-thrombotic agent. Inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP, arachidonic acid, and thrombin. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Coagulation factor X-activating enzyme heavy chain
description: Catalytic subunit of blood coagulation factor X-activating enzyme. Activates coagulation factor X (F10) by cleaving the Arg-Ile bond and is also able to activate coagulation factor IX (F9) and protein S (PROS1) by specific cleavage of Arg-Ile and Arg-Val bonds.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1ab
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1z
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1w
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: Omega-theraphotoxin-Asp1f
description: Inhibits voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav) in rat cerebellar granule cells (By similarity). Has insecticidal activity (By similarity).

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1aa
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: U1-theraphotoxin-Lp1b
description: Is toxic to mice but not to insects.

name: M-lycotoxin-Hc1a
description: Forms pore that permeabilize the cell membrane. Promotes efflux of calcium from synaptosomes, causes hemolysis, and dissipates voltage gradients across muscle membrane. Potently inhibits the growth of bacteria, yeast and Leishmania. Is lethal to lepidopteran larvae. May function both in the prey capture strategy as well as protection from infectious organisms arising from prey ingestion.

name: U1-segestritoxin-Sf1a
description: Is toxic to insects.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1ac
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: Potassium channel toxin TsTXK-beta
description: Specifically blocks voltage-gated potassium channels Kv4.2/KCND2. When measured at the peak current, the blocking effect of this toxin is about 65% and shows an IC(50)=652 nM (PubMed:27346450). However, when measured at a later moment of the depolarising test pulse (500 ms), a 100% block of the current is observed with an IC(50)=313 nM (PubMed:27346450). This may indicate a preference of the toxin for binding the inactivated state of the channel. The inhibition is completely reversible (PubMed:27346450). Using intraplantar injections on rat, this toxin induces overt nociception (licking and lifting behaviors) and decreases the mechanical nociceptive threshold (hyperalgesia). Furthermore, the hyperalgesia is prolonged when intrathecal injections are performed (PubMed:27346450).

name: Alpha-toxin 4
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. This toxin is active against insects and mammals.

name: Omega-oxotoxin-Ol1b
description: Weak blocker of vertebrate P/Q-, N- and L-type voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav1 and Cav2) (By similarity). Is both paralytic and lethal when injected into lepidopteran larvae. Is not toxic to mice.

name: U19-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Non-toxic to mice and insects.

name: U17-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Neurotoxin. Causes spastic paralysis and death in mice. Moderate inhibitor of L-type calcium channels (Cav1/CACNA1).

name: U18-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Neurotoxin. Causes spastic paralysis and death in mice by intracerebroventricular injection at dose levels of 3 ug per mouse.

name: U14-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Neurotoxin.

name: Chi-conotoxin-like PnMRCL-013
description: Chi-conotoxins inhibit the neuronal noradrenaline transporter (NET/SLC6A2).

name: Toxin AaHIT4
description: Has a toxic effect on insects and mammals and is capable of competing with anti-insect scorpion toxins for binding to the sodium channel (Nav) of insects. It also modulates the binding of alpha-type and beta-type anti-mammal scorpion toxins to the mammal sodium channel.

name: U2-sicaritoxin-Li1b
description: Toxin active against S.frugiperda larvae. May act on sodium channels (Nav) (By similarity).

name: Alpha-like toxin Lqh3
description: Binds voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. The dissociation is voltage-dependent. This alpha-like toxin is highly toxic to insects and competes with LqhaIT on binding to insect sodium channels. Differs from classical anti-mammalian alpha-toxins as it inhibits sodium channel inactivation in cell bodies of hippocampus brain neurons, on which the anti-mammalian Lqh2 is inactive, and is unable to affect Nav1.2 in the rat brain, on which Lqh2 is highly active. Moreover, its pharmacological properties are unique in that its binding affinity for insect channels drops >30-fold at pH 8.5 versus pH 6.5, and its rate of association with receptor site-3 on both insect and mammalian sodium channels is 4-15-fold slower compared with LqhaIT and Lqh2.

name: Vespulakinin-1
description: Induces smooth muscle contraction. May target bradykinin receptors (BDKRB). May cause hypotension.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 homolog vipoxin A chain
description: Heterodimer: postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 C
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Neutral phospholipase A2 muscarinic inhibitor
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits the muscarinic acetylcholine receptors (mAChR/CHRM) with no subtype selectivity. Shows catalytic activity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Neutral phospholipase A2 B
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Phospholipase B
description: May cause hemolysis or may be involved in protein folding and translation.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 CTs-G6
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that induces local edema a few hours after injection (5-10 ug) in the hind paw. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like 4a
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase that impairs hemostasis in the envenomed animal.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 B
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows potent hemolytic activity, and exhibits medium anticoagulant effects by binding to factor Xa (F10) and inhibiting the prothrombinase activity (IC(50) is 90 nM). It is one of the few phospholipases A2 capable of hydrolyzing the phospholipids of E.coli membranes in the presence of a bactericidal/permeability-increasing protein (BPI) of neutrophils. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Disintegrin CTF-II
description: Inhibits fibrinogen interaction with platelet receptors, and inhibits aggregation induced by ADP, thrombin, collagen and platelet-activating factor. Acts by binding to the alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) on the platelet surface (By similarity).

name: Polybia-CP
description: Chemotactic peptide for polymorphonucleated leukocytes (PMNL), but causing a very reduced hemolysis to rat erythrocytes and no mast cell degranulation activity at physiological concentrations. Potent antimicrobial peptide against Gram-positive bacteria B.subtilis CCT 2576 (MIC=15 ug/ml), and S.aureus ATCC 6538 (MIC=15 ug/ml). Has no antimicrobial activity against Gram-negative bacteria E.coli ATCC 25922 (MIC=250 ug/ml) and P.aeruginosa ATCC 15422 (MIC=250 ug/ml).

name: Protonectin
description: Shows potent antimicrobial action against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria (By similarity). This peptide shows potent histamine releasing activities on rat peritoneal mast cells.

name: Sylverin
description: This non-hemolytic peptide shows potent histamine releasing activities on rat peritoneal mast cells.

name: Delta-hexatoxin-Iw1a
description: Inhibits tetrodotoxin-sensitive sodium channels by binding to site 3. It slows the inactivation, causes a prolongation of action potential duration resulting in repetitive firing in autonomic and motor nerve fibers. Does not depolarize the resting potential. Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant sodium channels. This lethal neurotoxin is active on both insect and mammalian voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 BA1
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Alpha-conotoxin OmIA
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. This toxin blocks alpha-3/beta-2 (IC(50)=11 nM), alpha-7 (IC(50)=27.1) and alpha-6/alpha-3-beta-2-beta-3 (IC(50)=201 nM) subunits of nAChR.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 E
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin A
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin B
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S9-53F
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S3-24
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Alpha-latrocrustotoxin-Lt1a
description: Crustacean-selective presynaptic neurotoxin that induces neurotransmitter exocytosis. Binds to neurexin-1-alpha (NRXN1), adhesion G protein-coupled receptor L1 (ADGRL1, also known as latrophilin-1), and receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase S (PTPRS), and induces neurotransmitter exocytosis through two calcium-dependent mechanisms (membrane pore formation and signaling via latrophilin) and a yet to be defined calcium-independent mechanism (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S14-72F
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S8-51
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S13-69J
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S4-30
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 S11-61
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S5-32M
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 S15-109
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 S10-58F
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Toxin Td1
description: Beta toxins bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx J123
description: This recombinant toxin inhibits the mammalian voltage-gated potassium channels Kv1.3/KCNA3 and Kv1.2/KCNA2 in vitro with IC(50) of 0.79 nM and 26.4 nM, respectively.

name: Cytotoxin 2
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor nigrescinin-2
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.12
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels. Is less toxic than ergtoxin (AC Q86QT3).

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 1.12
description: Potent selective inhibitor of high conductance (maxi-K), different medium and small conductance calcium-activated potassium channels (KCa1.1/KCNMA1 and others), as well as a voltage-dependent potassium channel (Kv1.3/KCNA3>Kv1.2/KCNA2>Kv1.6/KCNA3>>Shaker/Sh). It blocks channel activity by a simple bimolecular inhibition process.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 1.13
description: Potent selective inhibitor of high conductance (maxi-K), different medium and small conductance calcium-activated potassium channels (KCa1.1/KCNMA1 and others), as well as a voltage-dependent potassium channel (Kv1.3/KCNA3>Kv1.2/KCNA2>Kv1.6/KCNA3>>Shaker/Sh). It blocks channel activity by a simple bimolecular inhibition process.

name: Cytotoxin 3d
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Cytotoxin 5
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Cytotoxin 3b
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Toxin ICK-24
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Cytotoxin 6
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Acidic phospholipase CHA-E6a
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows high lipolytic (1048 umol/mg/min) and weak ADP-induced platelet aggregation activities. Also shows weak anticoagulant activity (IC(50) is less than 1.0 uM). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Toxin ICK-9
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Thrombin-like enzyme bothrombin
description: Thrombin-like snake venom serine protease that clots fibrinogen by releasing fibrinopeptide A from the alpha chain of fibrinogen (FGA), induces platelet aggregation through its interaction with GPIb (GP1BA/GP1BB), and activates factor VIII (F8).

name: U10-hottentoxin-Hj2a
description: May block potassium channels.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor PIVL
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits trypsin. Exhibits an anti-tumor effect and displays integrin inhibitory activity without being cytotoxic. Is able to dose-dependently inhibit the adhesion, migration and invasion of human glioblastoma U87 cells. Also impairs the function of alphavbeta3 and to a lesser extent, the activity of alphavbeta6, alphavbeta5, alpha1beta1 and alpha5beta1 integrins.

name: Venom phosphodiesterase 1
description: Exhibits nuclease activity as well as pyrophosphatase and phosphatase activities, preferentially hydrolyzing nucleoside 5'-triphosphates over nucleoside 5'-diphosphates. Is inactive upon nucleoside 5'-monophosphates. Also inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP, but not by thrombin. Polyclonal antibodies raised against this do not abolish the lethal activity of the venom.

name: Disintegrin ussuristatin-2
description: Suppress platelet aggregation induced by ADP, collagen, thrombin, and epinephrine (IC(50)=170-330 nM). Also dose-dependently inhibits the adhesion of human melanoma cells to fibrinogen but not to fibronectin.

name: Scorpine-like
description: Has antimicrobial activity against S.aureus (78% growth inhibition at 1.8 uM).

name: Phospholipase A2 2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 13b
description: This peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent.

name: Thrombin-like enzyme gyroxin analog
description: Thrombin-like snake venom serine protease, that cleaves alpha-chain of fibrinogen (FGA) releases only fibrinopeptide A. Shows coagulant, esterase and amidase activities. Induces the barrel rotation syndrome in mice, which is manifested by gyroxin-like, rapid rolling motions. May also reversibly increase the permeability of the blood brain barrier (BBB) in mice.

name: Protein C activator
description: Snake venom serine protease that selectively cleaves the heavy chain of protein C (PROC). This activation is thrombomodulin-independent.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 12c
description: BPP-9a: inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) by a preferential interaction with its C-domain. May also potentiate the hypotensive effects of bradykinin.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 14a
description: This peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent. Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 11a-F has much lower activity than BPP-11a.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 7a
description: This peptide shows potent and long-lasting antihypertensive activity as well as a reduction of the heart rate. These effects may be explained by the agonistic activities of this peptide for the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor M1 (CHRM1) (EC(50)=0.25-0.31 uM), since these types of G-protein coupled receptor have been demonstrated to be active in the blood pressure control.

name: Chi-conotoxin-like Ar1248
description: Inhibits the neuronal noradrenaline transporter.

name: Chi-conotoxin-like Ar1311
description: Chi-conotoxins inhibit the neuronal noradrenaline transporter (NET/SLC6A2).

name: C-type lectin BML-2
description: Recombinant C-type lectin BML-2 is able to agglutinate erythrocytes. May be a calcium-dependent lectin.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.1
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.6
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 3.3
description: Blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.9
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.7
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 1.4
description: Blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 1.6
description: Blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.3
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 4.10
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin gamma-KTx 5.1
description: Reversibly blocks Kv11/ERG potassium channels.

name: U2-theraphotoxin-Lsp1a
description: Insecticidal neurotoxin.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 1
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor homolog beta-bungarotoxin B4 chain
description: Beta-2 bungarotoxin is a presynaptic neurotoxin of the venom. The B chain is homologous to venom basic protease inhibitors but has no protease inhibitor activity and is non-toxic (By similarity).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor Bi-KTI
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits plasmin (IC(50)=43.53 nM, Ki=3.6 nM). Acts as an antifibrinolytic agent. May act in a cooperative manner with the serine protease Bi-VSP (AC B5U2W0) to promote the spread of bee venom under anti-bleeding conditions.

name: Alpha-conotoxin-like Ac1.1a
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them.

name: Potassium channel toxin MeuTXK-beta-1
description: Has a low affinity binding to potassium channels of rat brain synaptosomes. Displays weak antibacterial activity against Stenotrophomonas sp. Strongly inhibits the development of the Plasmodium berghei ookinetes. Displays slight hemolytic effect on mouse erythrocytes. Induces cytolysis on Xenopus oocytes at high concentrations. Is not toxic on mice and on the insect Tenebrio molitor.

name: Alpha-insect toxin LqhaIT
description: Alpha toxins bind voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. The dissociation is voltage-dependent. This toxin is active on insects. It is also highly toxic to crustaceans and has a measurable but low toxicity to mice.

name: Mu-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Reversible inhibitor of neuronal sodium channels (Nav1.2/ SCN2A) that binds in proximity to site 1 and displays increasing affinity as the membrane potential is depolarized. Induces excitatory symptoms and spastic paralysis in mice.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor nigrescinin-1
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Toxin Lc a
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChRs), whereas it binds with a low affinity to neuronal alpha-7/CHRNA7 nAChRs.

name: Cystatin
description: Inhibits various C1 cysteine proteases including cathepsin L, papain and cathepsin B. This protein has no toxic activity and its function in the venom is unknown. It may play a role as housekeeping or regulatory protein (By similarity).

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 3.12
description: Potent inhibitor of voltage-dependent potassium channels, with a preference for Kv1.3/KCNA3 versus Kv1.2/KCNA2.

name: Alpha-conotoxin ArIA
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. ArIA acts as a competitive inhibitor and is 3-fold more potent on alpha-7 nAChRs (IC(50)=6 nM) than on alpha-3-beta-2 nAChR (IC(50)=18 nM).

name: Thrombin-like enzyme acutobin
description: Thrombin-like snake venom serine protease that coagulates human fibrinogen by hydrolysis of the alpha chains (FGA).

name: Snake venom serine protease Dav-PA
description: Snake venom serine protease that has fibrinogenolytic activities. Also possess esterolysis and amidolytic activities.

name: Snake venom serine protease Dav-KN
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Toxin Lc b
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChRs), whereas it binds with a low affinity to neuronal alpha-7/CHRNA7 nAChRs.

name: Kappa-scoloptoxin-Ssm3a
description: Toxin that inhibits voltage-gated potassium channel currents in DRG neurons. 200 nM of the toxin inhibits current amplitude by only 25% and even at concentrations up to 5 uM, the toxin does not inhibit all potassium currents. Shows signs of neurotoxicity including twitching, paralysis, and body contraction.

name: Weak neurotoxin 5
description: Binds with low affinity to muscular (alpha-1-beta-1-epsilon-delta/CHRNA1-CHRNB1-CHRNE-CHRND) and very low affinity to neuronal (alpha7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Kappa-scoloptoxin-Ssm2b
description: Toxin that inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Ts-K49a
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that induces local edema a few hours after injection (5-10 ug) in the hind paw, and shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog CTs-K49a
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Ts-R6
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that induces local edema a few hours after injection (5-10 ug) in the hind paw and shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog CTs-R6
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that induces local edema a few hours after injection (5-10 ug) in the hind paw, and shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Ts-A1
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows a moderate inhibition of ADP-induced human platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma. Exhibits high hydrolytic activities and prefers the anionic micelles (dPPC with deoxycholate) to the zwitterionic micelles (dPPC with Triton X-100). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog CTs-K49b
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Ts-K49b
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Ts-K49c
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that induces local edema a few hours after injection (5-10 ug) in the hind paw, and shows weak anticoagulant and myotoxic activities.

name: Snake venom metalloproteinase trimerelysin-2
description: Major venom non-hemorrhagic metalloproteinase.

name: Con-Ins Im1
description: This venom insulin facilitates prey capture by rapidly inducing hypoglycemic shock. Intraperitoneal injection of this peptide into zebrafish lowers blood glucose with the same potency than human insulin. In vivo, when applied to water, this peptide reduces overall locomotor activity of zebrafish larvae, observed as a significant decrease in the percentage of time spent swimming and movement frequency.

name: Conoporin-Cn1
description: Pore-forming protein that forms pores of around 1 nm and causes cardiac stimulation and hemolysis.

name: Mu-conotoxin-like T3.1
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) (By similarity). In vitro, this synthetic peptide displays a low blocking effect in mouse extensor digitorum longus muscles (IC(50)=616 nM).

name: Conotoxin CnIIIG
description: Shows a paralytic effect in fish.

name: Omega-conotoxin-like CnVIIE
description: Omega-conotoxins act at presynaptic membranes, they bind and block voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: Conotoxin CnIIIE
description: Shows a paralytic effect in fish.

name: Conotoxin CnIIIF
description: Shows a paralytic effect in fish.

name: Omega-conotoxin-like CnVIIJ
description: Omega-conotoxins act at presynaptic membranes, they bind and block voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: Omega-conotoxin-like CnVIIF
description: Omega-conotoxins act at presynaptic membranes, they bind and block voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: Omega-conotoxin-like CnVIIG
description: Omega-conotoxins act at presynaptic membranes, they bind and block voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: U7-theraphotoxin-Hhn1c
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U7-theraphotoxin-Hhn1d
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase/disintegrin
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase Eoc6: impairs hemostasis in the envenomed animal.

name: Amphipathic peptide CT1
description: Antimicrobial peptide that is rapidly bactericidal against Gram-positive bacteria (MIC=12.5 ug/ml against S.aureus, and MIC=100 ug/ml against M.luteus). Is also active against clinical antibiotics-resistant bacterial strains.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx Ctri9577
description: Recombinant peptide selectively inhibits mKv1.3/KCNA3 channel current with an IC(50) of 0.49 nM.

name: Omega-theraphotoxin-Gr2a
description: Blocks the low-voltage-gated calcium channels Cav3.1/CACNA1G. The inhibition is of about 30% of the current from Cav3.1 expressed in Xenopus oocytes. May also block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav).

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1q
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1r
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1s
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1t
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1u
description: Postsynaptic neurotoxin.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 14.1
description: Potential blocker of potassium channels.

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 daboiatoxin A chain
description: Heterodimer (A and B chains): phospholipase A2 that acts as a presynaptic neurotoxin and shows a PLA2 activity of 1377 umol/min/mg. In vivo, induces edema and produces neurotoxic symptoms in mice. Also exhibits indirect hemolysis, a strong myonecrotic activity and cytotoxicity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Supwaprin-a
description: Damages membranes of susceptible bacteria. Has no hemolytic activity. Not toxic to mice. Does not inhibit the proteinases elastase and cathepsin G.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor DrKIn-I
description: Serine protease inhibitor. Inhibits activated protein C (APC) with an IC(50) of 3.5 nM in the presence of heparin (to which it strongly binds) and an IC(50) of 88.9 nM in its absence. Other targets are also significantly inhibited in presence of heparin: trypsin (PRSS1) (45%), coagulation FXIa (F11) (40%), and plasmin (PLG) (70%). In vivo, synergizes with RVV-X in promoting coagulation in mice and by extension in Russell's viper bite patients.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog BmatTX-II
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that lacks enzymatic activity. Shows high myotoxic activity, neutrophil activation (demonstrated by activation induction of IL-1beta production), and slight cytotoxicity against tumor cell lines (T leukemia and breast adenocarcinoma).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor DrKIn-II
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits plasmin (90%) (Ki=0.19 nM), trypsin (70%), FXIa/F11 (37%) (Ki=6 nM) and FXa/F10 (20%), and prolonges the activated partial thromboplastin time. This antifibrinolytic property has been confirmed by a fibrin plate assay. Shows less antifibrinolytic activity that aprotinin. In vivo, reduces the bleeding time in a murine bleeding model, and prevents the increase of fibrin(ogen) degradation products in coagulation-stimulated mice.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor superbin-3
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor superbin-4
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Turripeptide OL22
description: Acts as a neurotoxin by inhibiting a ion channel.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 1.14
description: Potent blocker of both large-conductance calcium-activated potassium channels (KCa1.1/KCNMA1) and voltage-gated potassium channels (Kv1.3/KCNA3 and ERG1/Kv11.1/KCNH2).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like VAP2B
description: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like VAP2B: zinc metalloprotease that abolishes platelet aggregation induced by collagen, but has no effect on platelet aggregation induced by ADP or thromboxane analog. This inhibition may be due to its ability to bind collagen and block the binding site on collagen for platelets and/or to its ability to bind to the platelet alpha-2/beta-1 collagen receptor (ITGA2/ITGB1) to block its interaction with collagen and hence prevent platelet stimulation.

name: Snaclec convulxin subunit beta
description: Snake venom lectin that activates platelets by binding to the platelet collagen receptor glycoprotein VI (GP6) (PubMed:9153205). The indirect activation of integrin alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) also induced by the toxin is upstream the cytoskeletal translocation of GPIb, FcRgamma (FCER1G) and 14-3-3zeta (YWHAZ)(PubMed:16102113).

name: Snaclec convulxin subunit alpha
description: Snake venom lectin that activates platelets by binding to the platelet collagen receptor glycoprotein VI (GP6) (PubMed:9153205). The indirect activation of integrin alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) also induced by the toxin is upstream the cytoskeletal translocation of GPIb, FcRgamma (FCER1G) and 14-3-3zeta (YWHAZ)(PubMed:16102113).

name: Snake venom serine protease pallase
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Long neurotoxin homolog
description: Binds with low affinity and weakly inhibits muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Toxin ICK-14
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Neurotoxin
description: Neurotoxin. Decreases the action potential of myelinated nerves in mice and frogs.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 CHA-E6b
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows high lipolytic (1200 umol/mg/min) and weak ADP-induced platelet aggregation activities. Also shows weak anticoagulant activity (IC(50) of about 1.0 uM). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Toxin ICK-19
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Mu-theraphotoxin-Tp1a
description: Inhibits voltage-gated sodium channels without significantly altering the voltage dependence of activation or inactivation. The toxin preferentially inhibits hNav1.7/SCN9A (IC(50)=2.1 nM) > hNav1.6/SCN8A > hNav1.2/SCN2A > hNav1.1/SCN1A > hNav1.3/SCN3A channels in fluorescent assays. The toxin exhibits analgesic properties by reversing spontaneous pain induced in mice by intraplantar injection with OD1 (AC P84646), a scorpion toxin that potentiates hNav1.7/SCN9A.

name: Mesomartoxin
description: Recombinant toxin that reversibly blocks the voltage-gated potassium channels Shaker (IC(50)=0.054 nM), rKv1.2/KCNA2 (IC(50)=15.6 nM), and rKv1.3/KCNA3 (IC(50)=12.5 uM).

name: Delta-conotoxin TsVIA
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process. This toxin inhibits tetrodotoxin(TTX)-sensitive sodium channels. A test on mouse Nav1.6/SCN8A confirms this sensitivity.

name: Delta-conotoxin SuVIA
description: This toxin activates voltage-gated sodium channels. It shifts the voltage-dependence of activation to more hyperpolarized potentials but has only little effect on channel inactivation. It is active on Nav1.3/SCN3A (EC(50)=3.98 nM), Nav1.4/SCN4A (EC(50)=4.99 nM), Nav1.6/SCN8A (EC(50)=1.27 nM) and Nav1.7/SCN9A (EC(50)=2.42 nM) voltage-gated sodium channels. In vivo, it induces nocifensive or pain-like behaviors in mice when injected intraplantarly. This is coherent with the specific defensive role deduced from its proximal position in the venom gland.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 31.1
description: Voltage-gated potassium channel inhibitor. 1 uM of the native toxin inhibits rat Kv1.2/KCNA2 (100% inhibition), and drosophila Shaker IR/Sh (100%), human Kv1.3/KCNA3 (83%), rat Kv1.1/KCNA1 (32%) and rat Kv1.6/KCNA6 (21%).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Alpha-conotoxin LsIA
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. This toxin inhibits human alpha-7 (IC(50)=10.1 nM), rat alpha-3-beta-2 (IC(50)=10.3 nM) and rat alpha-3-alpha-5-beta-2 (IC(50)=31.2 nM).

name: Protein C activator
description: Snake venom serine protease that selectively cleaves the heavy chain of protein C (PROC). This activation is thrombomodulin-independent.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that has high lipolytic activity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 4
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that has high lipolytic activity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Conotoxin VxVIA
description: When injected intracranially in mice, induces a series of symptoms such as quivering, climbing, scratching, barrel rolling and paralysis of limbs. Unexpectedly, no effect is observed on ionic currents when tested on locust DUM neuron.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 BmjeTX-II
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that induces blockade of neuromuscular contraction in an indirectly stimulated chick biventer cervicis nerve-muscle preparation. Does not inhibit contraction of chick biventer cervicic nerve-muscle preparation in response to treatment with acetylcholine or KCl. The neuromuscular blockade is mediated by inhibitory action at the presynaptic motor nerve endings. Lyses skeletal myoblasts and myotubes in vitro, and intramuscular injection causes local muscle necrosis. Induces edema in the mouse foot pad. Induces a transient increase of IL-6 levels. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows myotoxicity and induces paw edema in mice (PubMed:17451767). Exhibits indirect hemolytic activity (PubMed:17451767). Inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP and collagen (PubMed:17451767). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (PubMed:17451767).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 10
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that has a strong dose-dependet anticoagulant effect. Intramuscular and intervenal injection causes muscle necrosis. Induces moderate edema in the mouse foot pad. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Snake venom metalloproteinase HF-1
description: Snake venom zinc metalloprotease that is weakly hemorrhagic and has Aalpha, Bbeta fibrinogenolytic activities. Cleaves the Aalpha chain of fibrinogen first, followed by the Bbeta chain and shows no effect on the gamma chain. Has caseinolytic activity. Induces dose-dependent edema.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 BmjeTX-I
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that induces a slight blockade of neuromuscular contraction in an indirectly stimulated chick biventer cervicis nerve-muscle preparation. Does not inhibit contraction of chick biventer cervicic nerve-muscle preparation in response to treatment with acetylcholine or KCl. The neuromuscular blockade is mediated by inhibitory action at the presynaptic motor nerve endings. Lyses skeletal myoblasts and myotubes in vitro, and intramuscular injection causes local muscle necrosis. Induces edema in the mouse foot pad. Induces a transient increase of IL-6 levels. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Alpha-toxin Bot1
description: Alpha toxins bind voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission.

name: Toxin LyeTx 1
description: Has antimicrobial activity against Gram-positive bacterium S.aureus (MIC=3.79 uM), Gram-negative bacterium E.coli (MIC=7.81 uM) and yeasts C.krusei (MIC=26.3 uM) and C.neoformans (MIC=13.2 uM). Has hemolytic activity against rabbit erythrocytes. Forms pores in lipid bilayers in vitro; pore formation is reduced when cholesterol is present in the bilayers.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 15.2
description: Blocks both human ERG1/Kv11.1/KCNH2 potassium channels (in a reversible manner) (PubMed:14599291) and A-type voltage-gated potassium channels (in an irreversible manner) (PubMed:11457451, PubMed:12473099, PubMed:12637022). May dispose of two functional faces (A and B); the two basic residues (Arg-40 and Lys-41) on the alpha-helix side of the peptide that blocks the hERG current (face A) and the typical dyad through which it blocks A-type currents on the beta-sheet side (face B) (PubMed:14599291). In adult rat brain, it binds to sites in the striatum, hippocampus, superior colliculus, and cerebellum. It shares the same target in rat brain than AaTX1 (AC Q867F4) and AmmTX3 (AC P60208).

name: Potassium channel toxin BmTXK-beta-2
description: Blocks voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Bucandin
description: This toxin is described as enhancing presynaptic acetylcholine release, but neither experimental results, nor references to other sources are available.

name: Candoxin
description: Binds and inhibits muscular and neuronal nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR). Is a reversible antagonist of muscle nAChR (alpha-1-beta-1-epsilon-delta/CHRNA1-CHRNB1-CHRNE-CHRND) (IC(50)=10 nM) and a potent and poorly reversible antagonist of the neuronal alpha-7 (CHRNA7) nAChR (IC(50)=50 nM). May exhibit differential affinities for the two binding sites on the muscle nAChR.

name: Cathelicidin-related peptide batroxicidin
description: Potent antimicrobial peptide against Gram-negative (MIC=0.25 ug/mL against E.coli ATCC 25922, MIC=1 ug/mL against P.aeruginosa) and Gram-positive bacteria (MIC=32 ug/mL against E.faecalis, MIC=32 ug/mL against S.aureus) (PubMed:25100358). Adopts an amphipathic alpha helical conformation, that may allow to partition into the target membrane (By similarity). Low hemolytic activities have been observed on mammalian cells (PubMed:25100358).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 BmTX-I
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows enzymatic activity in the presence of a synthetic substrate. In vitro, blocks the neuromuscular transmission in young chick biventer cervicis preparations. In mice, induces myonecrosis and a systemic interleukin-6 response upon intramuscular injection. Also induces edema and exerts a strong proinflammatory effect. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Serine proteinase-like BMK-CBP
description: Shows no significant hydrolytic activity. Binds in a dose-dependent manner to the cancer cell line MCF-7.

name: Alpha-latrotoxin-Lt1a
description: Presynaptic neurotoxin that induces exhaustive neurotransmitter release from vertebrate (but not invertebrate) nerve terminals and endocrine cells. Binds to neurexin-1-alpha (NRXN1), adhesion G protein-coupled receptor L1 (ADGRL1, also known as latrophilin-1), and receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase S (PTPRS), and induces neurotransmitter exocytosis through two calcium-dependent mechanisms (membrane pore formation and signaling via latrophilin) and a yet to be defined calcium-independent mechanism.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Tpu-K49b
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that lacks catalytic activity. Induces mild local edema a few hours after injection in the hind foot.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Tpu-K49a
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that lacks catalytic activity. Induces local edema a few hours after injection in the hind foot.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Tpu-E6a
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that impairs hemostasis. It weakly inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma from human and rabbit blood (15-25% of inhibition at 5-10 ug of enzyme), and dose-dependently inhibits blood coagulation, possibly by inhibiting thrombin activation. Exhibits high hydrolytic activities toward L-dipalmitoyl phosphatidylcholine. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 Tpu-G6D49
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that impairs hemostasis. It weakly inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma from human and rabbit blood (15-25% of inhibition at 5-10 ug of enzyme), and dose-dependently inhibits blood coagulation, possibly by inhibiting thrombin activation. Also induces local edema a few hours after injection in the hind foot. Exhibits high hydrolytic activities toward L-dipalmitoyl phosphatidylcholine. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog Tbo-K49
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that lacks catalytic activity. It induces local edema a few hours after injection in the hind foot.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Tpu-E6b
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that weakly inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma from human and rabbit blood (15-25% of inhibition at 5-10 ug of enzyme). Exhibits moderate hydrolytic activities toward L-dipalmitoyl phosphatidylcholine. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 Tbo-G6D49
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that impairs hemostasis. It weakly inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma from human and rabbit blood (15-25% of inhibition at 5-10 ug of enzyme), and dose-dependently inhibits blood coagulation, possibly by inhibiting thrombin activation. Exhibits strong hydrolytic activities toward L-dipalmitoyl phosphatidylcholine. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Tbo-E6
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that impairs hemostasis. It weakly inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma from human and rabbit blood (15-25% of inhibition at 5-10 ug of enzyme), and dose-dependently inhibits blood coagulation, possibly by inhibiting thrombin activation. Exhibits high hydrolytic activities toward L-dipalmitoyl phosphatidylcholine. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Cytotoxin 6
description: Basic protein that bind to cell membrane and depolarizes cardiomyocytes. This cytotoxin also shows lytic activities, on many other cells including red blood cells. Interaction with sulfatides in the cell membrane induces pore formation and cell internalization and is responsible for cytotoxicity in cardiomyocytes. It targets the mitochondrial membrane and induces mitochondrial swelling and fragmentation. Inhibits protein kinases C (By similarity). It binds to the integrin alpha-V/beta-3 with a moderate affinity (PubMed:16407244).

name: U4-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a
description: Neurotoxin active on both insects and mammals.

name: Snaclec 6
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: Mu-theraphotoxin-Hhn1b 1
description: Neurotoxin. Selectively blocks neuronal tetrodotoxin-sensitive voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) with an IC(50) of 44.6 nM. Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant voltage-gated sodium channels or calcium channels.

name: Mu-theraphotoxin-Hhn1b 2
description: Neurotoxin. Selectively blocks neuronal tetrodotoxin-sensitive voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) with an IC(50) of 44.6 nM. Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant voltage-gated sodium channels or calcium channels.

name: Mu-theraphotoxin-Hhn1c
description: Neurotoxin. Selectively blocks neuronal tetrodotoxin-sensitive voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant voltage-gated sodium channels or calcium channels.

name: Mu-theraphotoxin-Hhn1d
description: Neurotoxin. Selectively blocks neuronal tetrodotoxin-sensitive voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant voltage-gated sodium channels or calcium channels.

name: Omega-theraphotoxin-Hhn1f 1
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Snaclec 5
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: Omega-theraphotoxin-Hhn1b
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Omega-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 2
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Snaclec 1
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1f
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1a
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1d
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1e
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1b
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: U1-plectoxin-Pt1c
description: Potent toxin that may paralyze and/or kill insect pests such as H.virescens (lepidoptera), S.exigua (beet armyworm) and M.sexta (tobacco hornworm).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 DsM-S1
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that is neurotoxic. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: U28-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Has a vascular smooth muscle spasmogenic activity.

name: Snaclec 1
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog zhaoermiatoxin
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that induces myonecrosis, and edema. Has low myotoxic activity.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 15.6
description: Irreversibly blocks the A-type voltage-gated potassium channels in rat cerebellum granular cells (190 nM induce 50% inhibitory effect, PubMed:15369825) (IC(50)=190 nM, PubMed:18280256).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin 8
description: Inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation (probably by binding integrin alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3)) and degrades fibrinogen.

name: C-type lectin 9a
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: Venom phosphodiesterase 2
description: Exhibits nuclease activity as well as pyrophosphatase and phosphatase activities, preferentially hydrolyzing nucleoside 5'-triphosphates over nucleoside 5'-diphosphates. Is inactive upon nucleoside 5'-monophosphates. Also inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP, but not by thrombin. Polyclonal antibodies raised against this do not abolish the lethal activity of the venom.

name: Alpha-conotoxin-like Qc1.1c
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like brevilysin H6
description: Shows weak hemorrhagic activity. Rapidly degrades the alpha-chain of fibrinogen (FGA).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like BaG
description: Snake venom Zinc metalloproteinase that inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation and inhibits the alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) integrin, a fibronectin receptor. Has caseinolytic activity. Induces the detachment of cells that are bound to fibronectin.

name: U16-barytoxin-Tl1c
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U16-barytoxin-Tl1a
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U17-barytoxin-Tl1c
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 9.11
description: May play a role in blocking voltage-gated potassium channels Kv1.2/KCNA2, Kv1.3/KCNA3 and Kv1.6/KCNA6 to a lesser extent.

name: Augerpeptide-s7a
description: Elicits an uncoordinated twisting syndrome when injected into C.elegans, but has no effect on mice.

name: Augerpeptide-s11a
description: Does not elicit any observable symptomatology in C.elegans.

name: Mu-conotoxin CnIIIA
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). This synthetic toxin moderately blocks rNav1.1/SCN1A, rNav1.2/SCN2A, rNav1.3/SCN3A, rNav1.4/SCN4A, rNav1.5/SCN5A, and mNav1.6/SCN8A (PubMed:21652775). This block is very slowly reversible (PubMed:16533055). Causes seizures when injected intracranially into mice.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 12a
description: This peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent.

name: Toxin Acra3
description: The molecular target of Acra3 remains undiscovered. In vivo, induces severe neurotoxic events in mice such as excitability and convulsions, leading to the death of the animals within a few minutes after injection. Does not show toxicity in insects and crustaceans (PubMed:22819772). Exerts very strong cytotoxic effect on a mouse brain tumor cell line (BC3H1) with an IC(50) value of 5 mg/ml. It exerts its effects by inducing a stronger necrosis than apoptosis in BC3H1 cells (PubMed:24055552).

name: Serine protease harobin
description: Serine protein with fibrinolytic and fibrinogenolytic activities. Degrades Bbeta-chain (FGB) of fibrinogen first and then the Aalpha-chain (FGA). Gamma-chain (FGG) are also digested on prolonged incubation. In vitro, it cleaves high molecular weight (HMW) kininogen (KNG) releasing bradykinin that promotes vasodilation. In vitro and in vivo, it cleaves angiotensin-2 (AGT). This explains the reduction of blood pressure in hypertensive rats. Has also antithrombotic effects on thrombosis animal models.

name: Mu-conotoxin SIIIA
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). This toxin moderately blocks rNav1.1/SCN1A, rNav1.2/SCN2A, rNav1.3/SCN3A, rNav1.4/SCN4A, and mNav1.6/SCN8A.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog promutoxin
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that exhibits potent myotoxicity causing myonecrosis and myoedema in the gastrocnemius muscle of mice. Is also able to stimulate the release of IL12 (IL12A-IL12B), TNF-alpha (TNF), IL6 and IL1-beta (IL1B) from human monocytes, and induce IL2, TNFalpha and IL6 release from T-cells.

name: Stonustoxin subunit alpha
description: This lethal (towards mice) toxin induces hemolytic activities due to its ability to form pores in the cell membrane, elicits potent hypotension which is endothelium-dependent and appears to be mediated by the nitric oxide pathway and activation of potassium channels, displays edema-inducing activities, increases vascular permeability, induces endothelium-dependent vasorelaxation of isolated rat aorta, induces platelet aggregation, is myotoxic and interferes irreversibly with neuromuscular function.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Drs-PLA2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that has several activities. It exhibits anticoagulant activities (by inhibiting activated coagulation factor X (F10)), it shows hemolytic and cytotoxic activities (cytotoxic concentration(50)=65.8 nM), and inhibits cell migration in human skin melanoma cells (IC(50)=25.6 nM). In addition, it reduces tumor lung colonization of B16F10 melanoma cells in BALB/c mice by 65%. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Ts-A2
description: Exhibits moderate hydrolytic activities and prefers the anionic micelles (dPPC with deoxycholate) to the zwitterionic micelles (dPPC with Triton X-100). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 Ts-A5
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows a moderate inhibition of ADP-induced human platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma. Exhibits high hydrolytic activities and prefers the anionic micelles (dPPC with deoxycholate) to the zwitterionic micelles (dPPC with Triton X-100). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Snake venom serine protease rhinocerase
description: Snake venom serine protease that cleaves fibrinogen alpha and beta chains (FGA and FGB), but not gamma chains. Exhibits fibrinolytic and kininogenolytic. Preferentially cleaves after Arg and Lys residues.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 CTs-A2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows a moderate inhibition of ADP-induced human platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma. Exhibits moderate hydrolytic activities and prefers the anionic micelles (dPPC with deoxycholate) to the zwitterionic micelles (dPPC with Triton X-100). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Alpha-elapitoxin-Oh2b
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission (By similarity). Recombinant LNTX1 leads to a functional block of the muscle-type acetylcholine receptors. Has a cytotoxic activity. This neurotoxin is lethal (PubMed:16689684).

name: Disintegrin EMS11A
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of both the alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) and the alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) integrins to VCAM-1 and fibronectin respectively with almost the same degree of specificity. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin VB7A
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-2b/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin VB7B
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin EO5B
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. When it dimerizes with EO4A, it inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. When it dimerizes with EO5A, it inhibits the adhesion of the alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) integrin to VCAM-1. When it dimerizes either with EO4A or EO5A, the inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin VA6
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low, and there is no inhibition on alpha-1/beta-1 (ITGA1/ITGB1), alpha-2/beta-1 (ITGA2/ITGB1) and alpha-6/beta-1 (ITGA6/ITGB1).

name: Omega-agatoxin-Aa3a
description: Omega-agatoxin are antagonist of voltage-gated calcium channels. They block insect neuromuscular transmission presynaptically. Potent blocker of N- (Cav2.2/CACNA1B) and L-type (Cav1/CACNA1) calcium channels.

name: Disintegrin VLO4
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-2b/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin VLO5A
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of the alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) integrin to VCAM-1. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Ophiophagus venom factor
description: Complement-activating protein in cobra venom. It is a structural and functional analog of complement component C3b, the activated form of C3. It binds factor B (CFB), which is subsequently cleaved by factor D (CFD) to form the bimolecular complex OVF/Bb. OVF/Bb is a C3/C5 convertase that cleaves both complement components C3 and C5. Structurally, it resembles the C3b degradation product C3c, which is not able to form a C3/C5 convertase. Unlike C3b/Bb, OVF/Bb is a stable complex and completely resistant to the actions of complement regulatory factors H (CFH) and I (CFI). Therefore, OVF continuously activates complement (By similarity). As a result, OVF exhibits complement-depleting activity.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor textilinin-4
description: Serine protease inhibitor (By similarity). Does not inhibit plasmin, and does not reduce blood loss in the mouse tail vein blood loss model.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor textilinin-3
description: Serine protease inhibitor (By similarity). Does not inhibit plasmin, and does not reduce blood loss in the mouse tail vein blood loss model.

name: Toxin BmKaTx16
description: Binds voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor textilinin-6
description: Serine protease inhibitor (By similarity). Does not inhibit plasmin, and does not reduce blood loss in the mouse tail vein blood loss model.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor textilinin-5
description: Serine protease inhibitor (By similarity). Does not inhibit plasmin, and does not reduce blood loss in the mouse tail vein blood loss model.

name: Venom peptide 2-long
description: Has potent hemolytic activity against ovine erythrocytes at micromolar concentrations. Also exhibits strong antimicrobial activity against the fungi B.cinerea (MIC=0.5 ug/ml) and C.albicans, and moderate activity against the Gram-positive bacterium S.aureus (MIC=25 ug/ml) and the Gram-negative bacterium E.coli. Venom peptide 2-long has substantially lower antimicrobial activity against C.albicans (MIC=100 ug/ml) and bacteria than Orancis-protonectin but has equivalent activity against B.cinerea (MIC=0.5 ug/ml).

name: Eumenine mastoparan-OD
description: Has potent hemolytic activity against ovine erythrocytes at micromolar concentrations. Also exhibits strong antimicrobial activity against the fungi C.albicans and B.cinerea, and weaker activity against the Gram-negative bacterium E.coli and Gram-positive bacterium S.aureus.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin salmosin-3
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation (probably by binding integrin alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3)) and degrades fibrinogen.

name: Chymotrypsin-like protease VLCTLP
description: Snake venom serine protease with tyrosine-specific chymotrypsin-like activity. Hydrolyzes the N-acetyl-L-tyrosine ethyl ester (ATEE). Has weak fibrinogenolytic activity. Weakly hydrolyzes azocasein, Aalpha-chain (FGA) and more slowly Bbeta-chain (FGB) of fibrinogen. Optimal substrates are angiotensins I and II (AGT).

name: Neurotoxin alpha-KTx 12.7
description: Inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Toxin Td4
description: Beta toxins bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing.

name: Neurotoxin beta-KTx 14.3
description: Isoform 1 has a very weak effect to block voltage-gated potassium channel Kv1.1/KCNA1.

name: Lipolysis-activating peptide 1-beta chain
description: The homodimer inhibits HMG-CoA reductase (HMGCR) (32% of inhibition produced by 0.6 uM), a glycoprotein involved in the control of cholesterol biosynthesis. The inhibitory effects of bumarsin are seen at much lower concentrations (0.6 uM) than that for statins such as atorvastatin (5 mM) and simvastatin (10 uM). In addition to inhibition of HMG-CoA reductase, this protein lowers cholesterol levels by inducing steroid hormone synthesis via StAR, and by increasing reverse cholesterol transport mediated by the induction of ABCA1 and APOA1 (By similarity).

name: Omega-conotoxin Cl16a
description: Omega-conotoxins act at presynaptic membranes, they bind and block voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav). Reversibly blocks calcium current in the dorsal-root ganglion neurons of the rat (high voltage-activated channels but not low voltage-activated channels). Does not modify the voltage dependency of activation and inactivation.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 17.2
description: Inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Neurotoxin alpha-KTx 12.6
description: Inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Lipolysis-activating peptide 1-alpha chain
description: The heterodimer non-edited LVP1 induces lipolysis in rat adipocytes. Induction of lipolysis by LVP1 appears to be mediated through the beta-2 adrenergic receptor pathway (ADRB2) (By similarity).

name: Lipolysis-activating peptide 1-alpha chain
description: The heterodimer non-edited LVP1 induces lipolysis in rat adipocytes. Induction of lipolysis by LVP1 appears to be mediated through the beta-2 adrenergic receptor pathway (ADRB2) (By similarity).

name: Glutaminyl-peptide cyclotransferase
description: Responsible for the biosynthesis of pyroglutamyl peptides. Has a bias against acidic and tryptophan residues adjacent to the N-terminal glutaminyl residue and a lack of importance of chain length after the second residue. Also catalyzes N-terminal pyroglutamate formation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LarSicTox-alphaI-1
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Coagulation factor X isoform 2
description: Factor Xa is a vitamin K-dependent glycoprotein that converts prothrombin to thrombin in the presence of factor Va, calcium and phospholipid during blood clotting.

name: U20-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Omega-agatoxin are antagonists of voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav). Induces rapid general flaccid paralysis followed by death when injected into the cerebral ventricle of mice at dose levels of 3 ug per mouse.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 6.13
description: Antagonist of Kv1/KCNA potassium channels.

name: Alpha-like toxin BmK-M2
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. This toxin is active against mammals and insects.

name: U4-ctenitoxin-Co1c
description: Not toxic to mice by intracerebroventricular injection.

name: U14-ctenitoxin-Co1b
description: Not toxic to mice by intracerebroventricular injection.

name: U14-ctenitoxin-Co1c
description: Not toxic to mice by intracerebroventricular injection.

name: Toxin Ts4
description: Not toxic. Induces an immune response similar to that induced by whole venom. Induces a dose dependent release of the neurotransmitters glutamic acid and gamma aminobutyric acid from rat brain synaptosomes. Thus, polyclonal antibodies raised against this protein can neutralize the effects of the venom.

name: Gamma-conopressin vil
description: Targets vasopressin-oxytocin related receptors (By similarity). Binds calcium.

name: Snaclec A5
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: Phospholipase A1 1
description: Hydrolysis of phosphatidylcholine with phospholipase A2 (EC 3.1.1.4) and phospholipase A1 (EC 3.1.1.32) activities.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein
description: Blocks contraction of smooth muscle elicited by high potassium-induced depolarization, but does not block caffeine-stimulated contraction. May target voltage-gated calcium channels on smooth muscle (By similarity).

name: Dinoponeratoxin Dq-3104
description: The synthetic peptide has weak antimicrobial activity against Gram-negative bacterium E.coli ATCC 10536. Not active against Gram-positive bacteria B.amyloliquefacies S499, L.monocytogenes 2231 and S.aureus ATCC 29213, against Gram-negative bacteria P.putida BTP1 and P.aeruginosa PaO1, or fungi S.cerevisiae, R.mucilaginosa, C.cucumerinum, F.oxysporum and B.cinerea.

name: Dinoponeratoxin Dq-3162/Dq-3163/Dq-3178
description: The synthetic Dq-3162 peptide has antimicrobial activity against Gram-positive bacteria B.amyloliquefacies S499 (MIC=0.1 mM), L.monocytogenes 2231 and S.aureus ATCC 29213, against Gram-negative bacteria P.putida BTP1, P.aeruginosa PaO1 and E.coli ATCC 10536, and against the fungi S.cerevisiae, R.mucilaginosa and C.cucumerinum. Not active against the fungi F.oxysporum and B.cinerea.

name: Natriuretic peptide TNP-a
description: Exhibits vasoactive (PubMed:15652496) and hypotensive activity (By similarity). Is only weakly active on natriuretic peptide receptor-C (NPR3).

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like MVIA
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like EVIB
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like CVIE
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like CnVIA
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like SmVIA
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like MVIC
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Toxin ICK-10
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Disintegrin-like halysetin
description: Inhibits human platelet aggregation stimulated by collagen with an IC(50) of 420 nM.

name: U11-barytoxin-Tl1b
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-2
description: The hemorrhagic metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-1 is a potent inhibitor of collagen-induced platelet aggregation by blockage of alpha-2/beta-1 (ITGA2/ITGB1) integrin. It does not present any fibrinogen-clotting activity (By similarity).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-3
description: The hemorrhagic metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-1 is a potent inhibitor of collagen-induced platelet aggregation by blockage of alpha-2/beta-1 (ITGA2/ITGB1) integrin. It does not present any fibrinogen-clotting activity (By similarity).

name: Alpha-like toxin Lqh6
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. This toxin is highly toxic to insects and mice, and inhibits the binding of alpha-toxin to cockroach neuronal membranes.

name: Alpha-like toxin Lqh7
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. This toxin is highly toxic to insects and mice, and inhibits the binding of alpha-toxin to cockroach neuronal membranes.

name: Mambalgin-2
description: This three-finger toxin inhibits ASIC channels. It acts as a gating modifier toxin by decreasing the apparent proton sensitivity of activation and by slightly increasing the apparent proton sensitivity for inactivation (PubMed:24695733). It binds more tightly to the closed state and to a much lesser extent the inactivated/desensitized state of ASIC1a isoform of ASIC1 (PubMed:24695733). It binds mainly in a region of rat ASIC1a involving the upper part of the thumb domain (residues 'Asp-349' and 'Phe-350'), the palm domain of an adjacent subunit, and the beta-ball domain (residues 'Arg-190', 'Asp- 259', and 'Gln-260') (PubMed:24695733). The peptide exerts both stimulatory and inhibitory effects on ASIC1a (PubMed:24695733). It reversibly inhibits rat ASIC1a (IC(50)=21-55 nM), rat ASIC1b (IC(50)=103-192 nM), rat ASIC1a-ASIC1b (IC(50)=72 nM), rat ASIC1a-ASIC2a (IC(50)=246-252 nM) and rat ASIC1a-ASIC2b (IC(50)=61 nM) (PubMed:23034652, PubMed:23624383, PubMed:24323786, PubMed:24695733, PubMed:26991634). In vivo, it shows a potent naloxone-resistant analgesic effect against acute and inflammatory pain upon central and peripheral injection (By similarity). In addition, it also has an opioid-independent effect on both thermal and mechanical inflammatory pain after systemic administration and is effective against neuropathic pain (By similarity).

name: Disintegrin jarastatin
description: Binds alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGAV/ITGB1), alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) and alpha-M/beta-2 (ITGAM/ITGB2) integrins. Is a potent inhibitor of platelet aggregation induced by ADP, collagen, and thrombin. Induces neutrophil chemotaxis and inhibits the chemotaxis of human neutrophils toward fMLP, IL-8, and jarastatin itself. Directly activates an integrin-coupled signaling and modulate the MAPK pathway in different ways, leading the neutrophils to express different functional response. Jarastatin-treated neutrophils accumulates F-actin at the plasmalemma. Induces PTK2/FAK1 and phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) activation. Induces Erk-2 translocation to nucleus and a delay of the spontaneous apoptosis of neutrophils. Increases the IL-8 mRNA levels in neutrophils. When injected simultaneously with melanoma cells in mice, jarastatin, flavoridin (FL) and kistrin (KR), significantly reduce tumor lung colonization. Jarastatin inhibits B16F10 cell growth in vitro. When it interacts with melanoma cells, it induces actin cytoskeleton rearrangement, increasing actin polymerization and PTK2/FAK1 phosphorylation. Interferes with NF-kappaB translocation in melanoma cells.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 S2-22
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-4
description: The hemorrhagic metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like bothrojarin-1 is a potent inhibitor of collagen-induced platelet aggregation by blockage of alpha-2/beta-1 (ITGA2/ITGB1) integrin. It does not present any fibrinogen-clotting activity (By similarity).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin jararin
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation (probably by binding integrin alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3)) and degrades fibrinogen.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1b
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1c
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1q
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 12
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 15
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 13
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 14
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1a 16
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Hhn1d
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 Pto-N6
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that displays edema-inducing activities, as well as presynaptic neurotoxicity and myotoxicity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).
