name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin 2
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Pantinin-1
description: Amphipathic peptide that possesses relatively strong activities against Gram-positive bacteria and a fungus, but has very weak antimicrobial activities against Gram-negative bacteria. Also exhibits very low hemolytic activities against human erythrocytes (64 uM induce 21% of hemolysis). Minimal inhibitory concentration (MIC) are the following: 8 uM against S.aureus, 32 uM against B.magaterium, 32 uM against M.luteus, 28 uM against vancomycin-resistant Enterococci, 14 uM against methicillin-resistant S.aureus, 62 uM against E.coli, >87 uM against P.putida, >87 uM against K.oxytoca, 76 uM against E.cloacae, 72 uM against S.enterica and 16 uM against the fungus C.tropicalis.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating and C-type natriuretic peptides
description: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent (By similarity).

name: Cytotoxin 9
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming a pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity (By similarity). Preferentially binds acidic phospholipids like phosphatidylserine, phosphatidic acid and phosphatidyl glycerol (PubMed:26456928). Has hemolytic activity towards human erythrocytes (EC(50)=0.171 uM) and cytolytic activity towards various cell lines (PubMed:26456928).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 beta-bungarotoxin A2 chain
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits neuromuscular transmission by blocking acetylcholine release from the nerve termini. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 beta-bungarotoxin A1 chain
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits neuromuscular transmission by blocking acetylcholine release from the nerve termini. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Cathelicidin-related peptide lutzicidin
description: Potent antimicrobial peptide against Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria. Adopts an amphipathic alpha helical conformation, that may allow to partition into the target membrane. Low hemolytic activities have been observed on mammalian cells.

name: Disintegrin EO5A
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of the alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) integrin to VCAM-1. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin EO4A
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-2b/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low.

name: Disintegrin Eo1 subunit 1
description: Poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low (By similarity).

name: Disintegrin ocellatusin
description: The disintegrin ocellatusin-10c1 is a poor inhibitor of platelet aggregation. The disintegrin inhibits the adhesion of cells expressing the RGD-dependent integrin alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) to immobilized fibronectin. Inhibition on alpha-2b/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) is low, and there is no inhibition on alpha-1/beta-1 (ITGA1/ITGB1), alpha-2/beta-1 (ITGA2/ITGB1) and alpha-6/beta-1 (ITGA6/ITGB1) (By similarity).

name: Short neurotoxin C
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin B
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Snaclec lebecetin subunit alpha
description: Binds to the platelet GPIb/IX/V receptor system and inhibits ristocetin-induced platelet aggregation in human platelet-rich plasma. Strongly inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP, calcium ionophore, thrombin and collagen. Does not inhibit U46619-induced platelet aggregation.

name: Antimicrobial peptide scorpine-like-2
description: Has antimicrobial activity against yeasts and bacteria.

name: U21-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Protease. Hydrolyzes gelatin and succinyl casein.

name: U24-ctenitoxin-Pn1a
description: Cysteine proteinase inhibitor.

name: U7-ctenitoxin-Pr1a
description: Probable neurotoxin.

name: Snaclec lebecetin subunit beta
description: Binds to the platelet GPIb/IX/V receptor system and inhibits ristocetin-induced platelet aggregation in human platelet-rich plasma. Strongly inhibits platelet aggregation induced by ADP, calcium ionophore, thrombin and collagen. Does not inhibit U46619-induced platelet aggregation.

name: Snake venom metalloproteinase basparin-A
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that catalyzes the conversion of prothrombin (F2) to alpha-thrombin through formation of a thrombin intermediate, without requiring additional cofactors. Also inhibits collagen-dependent platelet aggregation in vitro, an effect that does not depend on proteolytic activity. In vivo, at low doses, induces defibrin(ogen)ation when injected intravenously or intramuscularly into mice. At higher doses, causes sudden death by intravenous administration due to numerous occluding thrombi in pulmonary vessels.

name: Delta-ctenitoxin-Pn1b
description: Neurotoxin. Induces immediate excitatory effects when injected intrathoracically in houseflies and cockroaches. Inhibits glutamate uptake in rat brain synaptosomes. It has no effect when intracerebroventricularly injected into mice.

name: Delta-hexatoxin-Mg1a
description: Selectively slows channel inactivation of mammalian Nav1.1/SCN1A, Nav1.3/SCN3A, and Nav1.6/SCN8A and shows higher affinity for insect Nav1/para channels (site 3). Induces tonic repetitive firing of nerve impulses in insect neurons accompanied by plateau potentials.

name: Beta-hexatoxin-Mg1a
description: Insect and vertebrate active toxin. Binds to site 4 of mammalian voltage-gated sodium channels and shifts the activation voltage of the mammalian Nav1.2a/SCN2A channel to more hyperpolarized voltages, whereas the insect channel, DmNav1 (para), is not affected. Competes for binding at site 3 of the insect sodium channel. Causes temporary paralysis when injected into lepidopteran larvae at 8.6 nmol/g. A low intracranial injection dose into mice causes lacrimation, closure of the eyes and sweating. A high injection dose causes extensive lacrimation and death.

name: U7-hextatoxin-Mg1a
description: Induces flaccid paralysis when injected into lepidopteran larvae. Intracranial injection into mice causes awkwardness of movement and laboured respiration until death.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like MTP9
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that may impair hemostasis in the prey.

name: C-type lectin BiL
description: Lectin displays hemagglutinating activity that is inhibited by galactose, lactose and EDTA. Is calcium-dependent.

name: U2-segestritoxin-Sf1d
description: Insecticidal toxin. Causes flaccid paralysis followed by death when injected into Heliothis virescens larvae. Does not induce any toxic effects when injected intravenously into adult mice at a dose of 1.25 mg/kg body weight (By similarity).

name: Mambalgin-3
description: This three-finger toxin inhibits ASIC channels (Ref.1). It acts as a gating modifier toxin by decreasing the apparent proton sensitivity of activation and by slightly increasing the apparent proton sensitivity for inactivation. It binds more tightly to the closed state and to a much lesser extent the inactivated/desensitized state of ASIC1a (By similarity). It binds mainly in a region of rASIC1a involving the upper part of the thumb domain (residues Asp-349 and Phe-350), the palm domain of an adjacent subunit, and the beta-ball domain (residues Arg-190, Asp-259, and Gln-260) (By similarity). The peptide exerts both stimulatory and inhibitory effects on ASIC1a (By similarity). It reversibly inhibits rASIC1a (IC(50)=17 nM), rASIC1b (IC(50)= 44 nM) and rASIC1a-rASIC2a (IC(50)=252 nM) channels (Ref.1). In vivo, it shows a potent naloxone-resistant analgesic effect against acute and inflammatory pain upon central and peripheral injection. In addition, it also has an opioid-independent effect on both thermal and mechanical inflammatory pain after systemic administration and is effective against neuropathic pain (By similarity).

name: Antimicrobial peptide TsAP-2
description: Has a high antimicrobial activity against the Gram-positive bacterium S.aureus (MIC 5 uM) and the yeast C.albicans (10 uM). Has a high hemolytic potency (18% at 20 uM). Also inhibits the growth of the five cancer cell lines tested.

name: U10-buthitoxin-Hj1a
description: May block potassium channels.

name: Beta-toxin Clt1
description: Beta toxins bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing.

name: Neurotoxin II.22.5
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Mu-conotoxin MrVIB
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels. Has a preference for Nav1.4/SCN4A over Nav1.2/SCN2A sodium channels. Blocks Nav channels by interacting mainly with the C-terminal part of the pore loop of domain-3. Also blocks fast-inactivating calcium current. Blocks Nav1.8/SCN10A sodium channels and has potent and long-lasting local anesthetic effects. Can also block propagation of action potentials in A- and C-fibers in sciatic nerve as well as skeletal muscle in isolated preparations.

name: Snaclec A3
description: Interferes with one step of hemostasis (modulation of platelet aggregation, or coagulation cascade, for example).

name: U10-theraphotoxin-Hs2a
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like BjussuMP-1
description: This protein is a zinc metalloprotease from snake venom that causes hemorrhage in mice after intradermal injection. It inhibits platelet aggregation induced by collagen and ADP. Has moderate edema activity, but no myotoxic activity. It hydrolyzes the Aalpha-chain and more slowly the Bbeta-chain of fibrinogen, without affecting the gamma-chains. It also shows proteolytic activity on casein. It is unable to clot plasma. It also shows bactericidal activity against E.coli and S.aureus.

name: Snake venom serine protease KN11
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease KN3
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease KN5
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease CL5
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease CL2
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease KN12
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease KN7 homolog
Snake venom serine protease KN10
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Kappa-theraphotoxin-Tb1a
description: Blocks Kv4.2/KCND2 voltage-gated potassium channels (IC(50) is 193.0 nM) by shifting the voltage-dependence of channel activation to more depolarized potentials. The toxin is thought to bind to the S3-S4 linker region of the voltage sensor domain.

name: Kappa-theraphotoxin-Tb1b
description: Low-affinity blocker of Kv4.2/KCND2 voltage-gated potassium channels. Is presumed to shift the voltage-dependence of channel activation to more depolarized potentials and to bind to the S3-S4 linker region of the voltage sensor domain.

name: Kappa-theraphotoxin-Tb1c
description: Blocks Kv4.2/KCND2 voltage-gated potassium channels probably by shifting the voltage-dependence of channel activation to more depolarized potentials and by binding to the S3-S4 linker region of the voltage sensor domain.

name: Neurotoxin 3FTx-8a
description: Binds with low affinity to muscular (alpha-1-beta-1-epsilon-delta/CHRNA1-CHRNB1-CHRNE-CHRND) and very low affinity to neuronal (alpha7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor bicolin
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits trypsin (Ki=550 nM) and thrombin (Ki=26000 nM). Exerts anticoagulant activity probably by the way of inhibiting thrombin.

name: Cytotoxin 3
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes (PubMed:8182052). In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Cytotoxin 1
description: This protein lyses red blood cells and has cardiotoxic and hypotensive activities.

name: Cytotoxin homolog 3
description: Has low cytotoxic activity.

name: Cytotoxin homolog 2
description: Has low cytotoxic activity.

name: Myotoxin-A
description: Cationic peptide that possesses multiple functions. It acts as a cell-penetrating peptide (CPP), and as a potent voltage-gated potassium channel (Kv) inhibitor. It exhibits antimicrobial activities, hind limb paralysis, and severe muscle necrosis by a non-enzymatic mechanism (By similarity). It also binds to sarcoplasmic reticulum calcium-ATPase (PubMed:1329655).

name: Myotoxin
description: Cationic peptide that possesses multiple functions. It acts as a cell-penetrating peptide (CPP), and as a potent voltage-gated potassium channel (Kv) inhibitor. It exhibits antimicrobial activities, hind limb paralysis, and severe muscle necrosis by a non-enzymatic mechanism (By similarity).

name: Delta-hexatoxin-Ar1a
description: Inhibits tetrodotoxin-sensitive voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) by binding to site 3. It slows the inactivation, causes a prolongation of action potential duration resulting in repetitive firing in autonomic and motor nerve fibers. Does not depolarize the resting potential. Does not affect tetrodotoxin-resistant sodium channels. This lethal neurotoxin is active on both insect and mammalian voltage-gated sodium channels.

name: Neurotoxin-1''
description: Alpha toxins bind voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. Is active against mammals and binds with high affinity rat brain synaptosomes.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 CTs-A1
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows a moderate inhibition of ADP-induced human platelet aggregation when tested on platelet rich plasma. Exhibits moderate hydrolytic activities and prefers the anionic micelles (dPPC with deoxycholate) to the zwitterionic micelles (dPPC with Triton X-100). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Neurotoxin homolog NL1
description: Antagonist of muscle and neuronal nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) with highest affinity for neuronal alpha-7 nAChRs.

name: Kunitz-type U15-theraphotoxin-Hs1c
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits chymotrypsin and blocks voltage-gated potassium channels (Kv).

name: Conophysin-R
description: Targets vasopressin-oxytocin related receptors (By similarity). No effect observed when injected into goldfish or into mice.

name: U1-theraphotoxin-Lsp1a
description: Is toxic to mice but not to insects.

name: U1-theraphotoxin-Lp1a
description: Is toxic to mice but not to insects.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like CnVIB
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process. This toxin acts on Nav1.4/SCN4A and Nav1.6/SCN8A (EC(50)=2.3 uM).

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 8.5
description: Selectively inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels Kv1.2/KCNA2 with an IC(50) of 183 nM.

name: Bengalin
description: Toxin that shows cardiotoxicity on isolated guinea pig heart and auricle and neurotoxicity on isolated rat phrenic nerve diaphragm. Shows antiosteoporosis activity in experimental rats. Also induces apoptosis against human leukemic cells (U937 and K562). Has no effect on normal human lymphocytes. Apoptosis has been evidenced from damaged nuclei, cell cycle arrest at sub G1 phase, increase of early apoptotic cells, augmentation of DNA fragmentation and also a reduction of telomerase activity. Also elicits loss of mitochondrial membrane potential (MMP) which induces cytochrome c release in cytosol, decreases heat shock protein (HSP) 70 and 90 expression, activates caspase-9, caspase-3, induces poly (ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) cleavage, and up-regulates caspase-3.

name: L-amino-acid oxidase
description: Catalyzes an oxidative deamination of predominantly hydrophobic and aromatic L-amino acids (L-Met, followed by L-Leu, L-Phe, L-Trp, L-Tyr, L-Ile), thus producing hydrogen peroxide that may contribute to the diverse toxic effects of this enzyme. Exhibits diverse biological activities, such as apoptosis, cytotoxicity towards several cancer cell lines, induction of platelet aggregation, induction of moderate mouse paw edema, and antibacterial activities against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. Unlike other snake venom L-amino acid oxidases, does not induce hemorrhage (with 50 ug of enzyme). May also act in hemolysis, and antiparasitic activities. Effects of snake L-amino oxidases on platelets are controversial, since they either induce aggregation or inhibit agonist-induced aggregation. These different effects are probably due to different experimental conditions.

name: L-amino-acid oxidase
description: Catalyzes an oxidative deamination of predominantly hydrophobic and aromatic L-amino acids (L-Ile followed by L-Phe, L-Met, L-Val, L-Arg, L-Leu), thus producing hydrogen peroxide that may contribute to the diverse toxic effects of this enzyme. Exhibits diverse biological activities, such as hemorrhage (minimum hemorrhagic dose of 10 ug), and apoptosis. May also induce hemolysis, edema, antibacterial and antiparasitic activities. May also regulate platelet aggregation. Effects of snake L-amino oxidases on platelets are controversial, since they either induce aggregation or inhibit agonist-induced aggregation. These different effects are probably due to different experimental conditions.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like CnVID
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process. This toxin acts on Nav1.2/SCN2A, Nav1.3/SCN3A and Nav1.6/SCN8A (EC(50)=1.7 uM).

name: Delta-conotoxin-like CnVIC
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process. This toxin acts on Nav1.2/SCN2A, Nav1.4/SCN4A, Nav1.5/SCN5A (weak activity), Nav1.6/SCN8A (EC(50)=2.5 uM).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase/disintegrin
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase TM-3: fibrin(ogen)olytic protease which cleaves the Aalpha chain of fibrinogen (FGA) first followed by the Bbeta chain (FGB) and shows relatively low activity on the gamma chain (FGG).

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 2.3
description: Inhibitor of voltage-gated potassium channels (Kv). It is capable of displacing the binding of radio-labeled noxiustoxin (AC P08815) to rat brain synaptosomes with high affinity (about 100 pM). It is also capable of inhibiting transient potassium-currents (resembling I(A)-type currents), in cultured rat cerebellar granule cells. About 50% of the peak currents are reduced by application of a 1.5 uM solution of this toxin.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 1.2
description: Blocks calcium-activated potassium channels (Kd=43 nM on KCa1.1/KCNMA1). Has a potent presynaptic facilitatory action, with less effect on direct muscle stimulation.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like MTP4
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that may impair hemostasis in the prey.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein
description: Blocks olfactory (CNGA2) and retinal (CNGA1) CNG channel currents. Does not affect neither depolarization- nor caffeine-induced contraction of smooth muscle (By similarity).

name: Long neurotoxin 43
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Phospholipase A2 147
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Vespryn-21
description: Neurotoxin that produces dose-dependent hypolocomotion and hyperalgesia in mice. May directly act on the central nervous system, as it is 6500-fold more potent when administered intracerebroventricularly than intraperitoneal (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase A2 PS22
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits collagen-induced platelet aggregation. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase-B 81
description: May cause hemolysis.

name: Venom prothrombin activator vestarin-D1
description: Snake prothrombin activator that attacks the hemostatic system of prey. This protein is functionally similar to blood coagulation factor Xa (By similarity).

name: Short neurotoxin SNTX-1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX-2
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChRs), whereas it binds with a low affinity to neuronal alpha-7/CHRNA7 nAChRs.

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX-1
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: AVIToxin-VAR1
description: Potent agonist for both PKR1/PROKR1 and PKR2/PROKR2. Potently contracts gastrointestinal (GI) smooth muscle.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR1
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: AVIToxin-VAR2
description: Potent agonist for both PKR1/PROKR1 and PKR2/PROKR2. Potently contracts gastrointestinal (GI) smooth muscle.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR4
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR5
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein
description: Blocks olfactory (CNGA2) and retinal (CNGA1) cyclic nucleotide-gated (CNG) ion channel currents. Does not inhibit retinal (CNGA3) currents. It forms high-affinity contacts with the pore turret region and most likely inhibits CNG channel current by blocking the external entrance to the transmembrane pore. Does not affect neither depolarization- nor caffeine-induced contraction arterial smooth muscle (By similarity).

name: Venom prothrombin activator vestarin-D2
description: Snake prothrombin activator that attacks the hemostatic system of prey. This protein is functionally similar to blood coagulation factor Xa (By similarity).

name: L-amino-acid oxidase
description: Catalyzes an oxidative deamination of predominantly hydrophobic and aromatic L-amino acids, thus producing hydrogen peroxide that may contribute to the diverse toxic effects of this enzyme. Exhibits diverse biological activities, such as hemorrhage, hemolysis, edema, antibacterial and antiparasitic activities, as well as regulation of platelet aggregation. Its effect on platelets is controversial, since it either induces aggregation or inhibits agonist-induced aggregation. These different effects are probably due to different experimental conditions (By similarity). Inhibits growth of B.subtilis strain ATCC 6633 (MIC=32 uM), E.faecalis strain ATCC 12953 (MIC=32 uM), S.aureus strain ATCC 29213 (MIC=32 uM), S.pyogenes strain ATCC 19615 (MIC=8 uM), E.coli strain ATCC 8739 (MIC=4 uM), K.pneumoniae strain ATCC 13885 (MIC=2 uM), P.mirabilis strain ATCC 25933 (MIC=2 uM), P.aeruginosa strain ATCC 15442 (MIC=8 uM) and S.typhimurium strain ATCC 14028 (MIC=8 uM).

name: Nawaprin
description: Damages membranes of susceptible bacteria. Has no hemolytic activity. Not toxic to mice. Does not inhibit the proteinases elastase and cathepsin G.

name: Erabutoxin b
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChRs), and with low affinity to neuronal alpha-7 nAChRs and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission. Produces peripheral paralysis by blocking neuromuscular transmission at the postsynaptic site.

name: Snake venom serine protease Afaacytin alpha/beta/beta' chains
description: Snake venom serine protease that exhibits alpha-fibrinase and beta-fibrinogenase activities. It replaces missing factors VIII (F8) and IX (F9) in deficient plasmas by activating purified human factor X (F10) into factor Xa. It releases serotonin from platelets and induces platelet aggregation in human (but not in rabbit). Has caseinolytic, arginine-esterase and amidase activities.

name: Disintegrin lachesin
description: Inhibits fibrinogen interaction with platelets. Acts by binding to alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) on the platelet surface and inhibits aggregation induced by ADP, thrombin, platelet-activating factor and collagen.

name: Gamma-conotoxin-like de7a
description: Gamma-conotoxins may act on voltage-gated non-specific cation pacemaker channels (HCN).

name: Gamma-conotoxin-like As7a
description: Gamma-conotoxins may act on voltage-gated non-specific cation pacemaker channels (HCN) (By similarity). Elicits toxic effects in the freshwater snail Pomacea paludosa after intramuscular injection, but it has no effect when injected intracerebrally into mice.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Cg1b
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Cg1a
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Cg1a
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U1-theraphotoxin-Cg1a 2
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U2-theraphotoxin-Cg1a
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: Kappa-theraphotoxin-Cg1b
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Cg1c
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U3-theraphotoxin-Cg1b
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: Conotoxin Ge14.1
description: Inhibits Sf9 cell growth.

name: Mu-conotoxin BuIIIB
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). This synthetic toxin potently blocks rNav1.2/SCN2A, and rNav1.4/SCN4A. It also moderately blocks rNav1.1/SCN1A, rNav1.3/SCN3A, rNav1.5/SCN5, and mNav1.6/SCN8A. The block of SCN4A is very slowly reversible.

name: Mu-conotoxin BuIIIC
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels. Extremely potent inhibitor of Nav1.4/SCN4A. The inhibition is very slowly reversible.

name: Mu-conotoxin BuIIIA
description: Mu-conotoxins block voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav). This synthetic toxin potently blocks rNav1.2/SCN2A, and rNav1.4/SCN4A. It also moderately blocks rNav1.1/SCN1A, rNav1.3/SCN3A, rNav1.5/SCN5A, and mNav1.6/SCN8A. The inhibition is reversible.

name: M-zodatoxin-Lt8h
description: Insecticidal, cytolytic and antimicrobial peptide. Has insecticidal activity against the flesh fly S.carnaria. Has antibacterial activity against the Gram-negative bacteria E.coli. Forms voltage-dependent, ion-permeable channels in membranes. At high concentration causes cell membrane lysis.

name: Phospholipase D Ls4SicTox-alphaIII1i
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D Ls4SicTox-alphaIII1ii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LlSicTox-alphaIII3ii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Conotoxin Rg11a
description: Neurotoxin. Elicits hypersensibility when injected intracranially in mice. May act via potassium channel currents.

name: Hypotensin-2
description: Agonist of the B2 bradykinin receptor (BDKRB2). Potentiates the hypotensive effect of bradykinin (BK) and induces a direct vasorelaxing effect, independently of BK, by endothelium- and nitric oxide (NO)-dependent mechanisms in rat aortic ring preparations. Does not inhibit the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE).

name: Phospholipase D LhSicTox-alphaIV1ii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LhSicTox-alphaIV1iii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LhSicTox-alphaIV2
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LamSicTox-alphaIV1i
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LamSicTox-alphaIV1ii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase A2
description: Toxic phosholipase A2, which may catalyze the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides. Inhibits both skeletal (RYR1) and cardiac (RYR2) ryanodine receptors (calcium release channels). Probably blocks ryanodine receptors by generating a lipid product (By similarity).

name: Beta-insect depressant toxin LqhIT2
description: Depressant insect beta-toxins cause a transient contraction paralysis followed by a slow flaccid paralysis. They bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing. This toxin is active only on insects.

name: Translationally-controlled tumor protein homolog
description: Venom protein that causes edema, enhances vascular permeability and is likely related to the inflammatory activity of the venom.

name: Plancitoxin-1
description: Hydrolyzes DNA with an optimum pH of 7.2. Is potently hepatotoxic. It induces caspase-independent apoptosis (on rat liver cells) through the following procedure: binding to a specific receptor in the cytoplasmic membrane, entering the cell, entering the nucleus and degrading DNA.

name: Agelaia-mastoparan
description: Hemolytic mast cell degranulator, presenting no antimicrobial action and no chemotaxis for polymorphonucleated leukocytes (PMNL).

name: Myotoxin TmC4-47.2
description: Able to depolarize frog skeletal muscle fibers, but has no effects on squid giant axons. Tetrodotoxin is able to partially antagonize the depolarization. Induces myonecrosis.

name: Venom plasminogen activator TSV-PA
description: Snake venom serine protease that activates plasminogen.

name: Beta-fibrinogenase mucrofibrase-5
description: Snake venom serine protease with strong beta-fibrinogenolytic activities, angiotensin I (AGT)-degrading activities and strong kallikrein-like activities in vitro, releasing bradykinin from kininogen (KNG1). Intravenous injection mildly lowers blood pressure in experimental rats, which may be explained by the action on angiotensin I and kininogen.

name: Beta-fibrinogenase mucrofibrase-4
description: Snake venom serine protease with fibrinogenolytic activities. Cleaves beta-chain of fibrinogen (FGB) efficiently and shows relatively lower activity on alpha-chain.

name: Phospholipase D LiSicTox-alphaIA2bi
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LiSicTox-alphaIA2bii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase/disintegrin
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase saxin: impairs hemostasis in the envenomed animal.

name: Thrombin-like enzyme saxthrombin
description: Thrombin-like snake venom serine protease that shows strong blood coagulation activity in vitro.

name: Phospholipase D LiSicTox-alphaIA2aiii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Induces complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SaSicTox-betaIIB1
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Short neurotoxin 3FTx-Oxy4
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 7.1
description: Potent inhibitor of the A-type voltage-gated potassium channels. Most potent inhibitor of Kv1.2/KCNA2 channels. Reversibly block the Shaker B potassium-channels (Kv1.1 sub-family).

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 7.2
description: Potent inhibitor of the A-type voltage-gated potassium channels. Most potent inhibitor of Kv1.2/KCNA2 channels. Reversibly block the Shaker B potassium-channels (Kv1.1 sub-family), but with a lower affinity than PiTX-K alpha.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 beta-bungarotoxin A5 chain
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that inhibits neuromuscular transmission by blocking acetylcholine release from the nerve termini. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Snake venom serine protease pallabin
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Peptide BmKa2
description: Highly acidic peptide that may have antibacterial activity.

name: Snaclec mucrocetin subunit alpha
description: Platelet-agglutinating factor that acts in a vWF-independent manner. Binds specifically to platelet GPIbalpha (GP1BA) to a distinct binding site from that of flavocetin-A.

name: Snake venom serine protease Dav-X
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Alpha-conotoxin-like Pu1.1
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 6.8
description: Blocker of voltage-gated potassium channels.

description: Blocker of voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 6.6

description: Blocker of voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Alpha-conotoxin-like Leo-A1
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 homolog BaTX
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 homolog that lacks enzymatic activity but is myotoxic. Induces a temperature and dose-dependent complete and irreversible blockade of neuromuscular contraction in an indirectly stimulated chick biventer cervicic nerve-muscle preparation and mouse phrenic nerve-diaphragm preparation. Does not inhibit contraction of chick biventer cervicic nerve-muscle preparation in response to treatment with acetylcholine or KCl. The neuromuscular blockade produced by BaTX is mediated by inhibitory action at the presynaptic motor nerve endings. Rapidy lyses skeletal myoblasts in vitro, and intramuscular injection in mice causes severe muscle necrosis by a non-enzymatic mechanism. Induces a dose-dependent edema in the mouse foot pad.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 8.2
description: Blocks small conductance calcium-activated potassium channels (KCNN, SK). Low toxicity by intracerebroventricular injection into mice.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 9.2
description: Blocks small conductance calcium-activated potassium channels (KCNN, SK). Low toxicity by intracerebroventricular injection into mice.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 SpII RP4
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 3.10
description: Inhibits insect potassium channel. Is at least a hundred-fold more potent against the Drosophila Shaker channel than towards its mammalian homologs Kv1.1/KCNA1 and Kv1.3/KCNA3.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 3.11
description: Blocks the voltage-gated potassium channel Kv1.3/KCNA3, with an IC(50) of 7.2 nM.

name: Disintegrin tzabcanin
description: Inhibits fibrinogen interaction with platelets. Acts by binding to alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) on the platelet surface and inhibits aggregation induced by ADP, thrombin, platelet-activating factor and collagen (By similarity). Inhibits cell adhesion to vitronectin, probably by blocking its receptor integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3), and to fibronectin in vitro (PubMed:26163300, PubMed:27060015). Shows little to no cytotoxicity in vitro (PubMed:26163300, PubMed:27060015).

name: Neurotoxin beta-KTx 31.1
description: Inhibits voltage-gated potassium channel.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits trypsin (Ki=0.0035 nM).

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX37
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin SNTX6
description: This three-finger toxin binds and inhibits the nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Short neurotoxin SNTX11
description: This three-finger toxin binds and inhibits the nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Short neurotoxin SNTX14
description: This three-finger toxin binds and inhibits the nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX8
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX22
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX28
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that displays low systemic toxicity and causes severe symptoms only at very high concentrations (15 mg/kg). Has neither coagulant nor anticoagulant activity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Long neurotoxin LNTX1
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission (By similarity). Recombinant LNTX1 leads to a functional block of the muscle-type acetylcholine receptors. Has a cytotoxic activity (PubMed:16689684).

name: Peptide BmKb1
description: Has antibacterial activity against Gram-positive bacteria S.aureus, M.luteus, B.subtilis, and Gram-negative bacteria E.coli, and P.aeruginosa.

name: C-type lectin lectoxin-Phi2
description: Mannose-binding lectin which recognizes specific carbohydrate structures and agglutinates a variety of animal cells by binding to cell-surface glycoproteins and glycolipids. May be a calcium-dependent lectin (By similarity).

name: C-type lectin lectoxin-Phi1
description: Mannose-binding lectin which recognizes specific carbohydrate structures and agglutinates a variety of animal cells by binding to cell-surface glycoproteins and glycolipids. May be a calcium-dependent lectin (By similarity).

name: C-type lectin lectoxin-Lei1
description: Lectin which recognizes specific carbohydrate structures and agglutinates a variety of animal cells by binding to cell-surface glycoproteins and glycolipids. May be a calcium-dependent lectin (By similarity).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 P'513
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Fulgimotoxin
description: Reptile-specific three-finger toxin that is lethal at low doses for lizards, but not for mice. Probably acts as a neurotoxin.

name: Alpha-elapitoxin-Dpp2d
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (IC(50)=114+-37 nM) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) (IC(50)=58+-24 nM) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission. Competitive radioligand binding assays also demonstrate that this toxin competes with epibatidine binding to the Lymnea stagnalis acetylcholine-binding protein (Ls-AChBP) (IC(50)=4.9+-2.3 nM).

name: Omega-hexatoxin-Hv1a
description: Reversibly and voltage-independently blocks both mid-low- (M-LVA) and high-voltage-activated (HVA) calcium channels in cockroach DUM neurons. Lethal to many insect orders but not toxic to mice or rabbits. May target the insect high-voltage-activated calcium channel Dmca1D. Also inhibits acarines calcium channels. An extremely high toxin concentration partially inhibits Cav1.2/CACNA1C, Cav2.1/CACNA1A and Cav2.2/CACNA1B calcium channel of rats. As for omega-AcTx-Hv2a, the phenotypic effect of injection of this toxin into lone star ticks (Amblyomma americanum) is curling of all eight legs into closed loops.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor ki-VN
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Snake venom serine protease nikobin
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Pilosulin-3a
description: Has no hemolytic activity.

name: Antimicrobial peptide Con22
description: Hemolytic and antibacterial and antifungal peptide.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 nigroxin A
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that has only a weak enzymatic activity. It has a myotoxic activity in vivo (dystrophic effect). PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2 5
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Snake venom serine protease catroxase-1
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Snake venom serine protease catroxase-2
description: Snake venom serine protease that may act in the hemostasis system of the prey.

name: Beta-insect depressant toxin Lqh-dprIT3a
description: Depressant insect beta-toxins cause a transient contraction paralysis followed by a slow flaccid paralysis. They bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and block action potentials, primarily by depolarizing the axonal membrane and suppressing the sodium current. This depressant toxin is active only on insects. It is found in a relatively small amount in the venom, and its activity on insects is 10-fold higher compared to other known depressant toxins.

name: Beta-insect depressant toxin Lqh-dprIT3c
description: Depressant insect beta-toxins cause a transient contraction paralysis followed by a slow flaccid paralysis. They bind voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and block action potentials, primarily by depolarizing the axonal membrane and suppressing the sodium current. This depressant toxin is active only on insects. It is found in a relatively small amount in the venom, and its activity on insects is 10-fold higher compared to other known depressant toxins.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide S
description: This peptide potentiates the effects of bradykinin on smooth muscle, and inhibits the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) in vitro.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide 11
description: This peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent (By similarity).

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide TmF
description: This peptide both inhibits the activity of the angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) and enhances the action of bradykinin by inhibiting the peptidases that inactivate it. It acts as an indirect hypotensive agent.

name: Bradykinin-potentiating peptide POL-236
description: This peptide acts as a hypotensive peptides, but its action is not related to angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibition.

name: Venom serine proteinase-like protein 2
description: Not known; probably has lost its catalytic activity.

name: Factor V activator
description: Venom serine protease that converts factor V (F5) to the active form Va in the presence of calcium ions and phospholipids. It cleaves the Arg(1545)-Ser(1546) linkage in the human factor V molecule. Has hydrolytic activities against BAEE (1.2 U/mg), TAME, and Pro-Phe-Arg-MCA (4.9 U/mg). Shows coagulant activity.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Toxin S5C10
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Snake venom serine protease jerdonase
description: Multifunctional venom serine protease that has fibrino(geno)lytic activity towards the A alpha-chain of human fibrinogen (FGA) and a slow activity towards the B beta-chain (FGB). Also hydrolyzes bovine low-molecular-mass kininogen and releases bradykinin. Catalyzes the hydrolysis of BAEE, S-2238 and S-2302.

name: Beta-fibrinogenase jerdofibrase
description: Fibrin(ogen)olytic serine protease degrades Bbeta-chain of human fibrinogen (FGB) and shows a lower activity on Aa-chain (FGA). Also degrades fibrin directly. Releases fibrinopeptide B and a small amount of fibrinopeptide A. Has also be shown to catalyze the hydrolysis of some chromogenic substrates such as S2238, S2160, S2302 and S2251.

name: Toxin S5C1
description: Inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation and inhibits the binding of purified platelet fibrinogen receptor alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) to immobilized fibrinogen.

name: Synergistic-type venom protein C8S2, chain 1
description: This protein shows a synergetic toxic effect in that it enhances the toxicity of an angusticeps type toxin.

name: Synergistic-type venom protein C8S2, chain 2
description: This protein shows a synergetic toxic effect in that it enhances the toxicity of an angusticeps type toxin.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Toxin FS-2
description: Specific blocker of the voltage-dependent L-type calcium channel (Cav1/CACNA1) (PubMed:8826098). Inhibits cardiac contractions (By similarity).

name: Snaclec anticoagulant protein subunit B
description: Anticoagulant protein which binds to the gamma-carboxyglutamic acid-domain regions of factors IX and factor X in the presence of calcium with a 1 to 1 stoichiometry. Also inhibits platelet aggregation by binding to platelet glycoprotein Ibalpha (GP1BA) and functioning as a blocker of vWF. Is devoid of hemorrhagic and lethal activities. Possess antithrombotic and thrombolytic activities. Also hydrolyzes the Aalpha-chain of fibrinogen. Does not affect the Bbeta-chain and the gamma chain (By similarity).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor PILP-2
description: Shows weak binding and inhibition of MMP-2 and shows an activity in inhibiting migration and invasion of neuroblastoma.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor PILP-1
description: Serine protease inhibitor that inhibits trypsin (Ki=55.62 nM).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor PILP-3
description: Binds and inhibits MMP-2 and shows an activity in inhibiting migration and invasion of neuroblastoma. Intact C-terminus is crucial to the activities of this protein (PubMed:19706303).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase/disintegrin
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase: impairs hemostasis in the envenomed animal (By similarity). This product has not been identified in the venom.

name: Pandinin-1
description: Disrupts cell membranes through formation of pores. Strong antimicrobial activity against Gram-positive bacteria B.subtilis, S.epidermidis, E.faecalis and S.aureus. Less active against Gram-negative bacteria P.aeruginosa and E.coli. Has no antifungal or hemolytic activity.

name: Omega-hexatoxin-Hi1e
description: Inhibits insect, but not mammalian, voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein TEL1
description: Blocks contraction of smooth muscle elicited by high potassium-induced depolarization, but does not block caffeine-stimulated contraction. May target voltage-gated calcium channels on smooth muscle (By similarity).

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein TRI1
description: Blocks contraction of smooth muscle elicited by high potassium-induced depolarization, but does not block caffeine-stimulated contraction. May target voltage-gated calcium channels on smooth muscle (By similarity).

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR9
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR10
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein VAR11
description: Blocks ryanodine receptors, and potassium channels.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor B5
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Omega-hexatoxin-Hvn1b
description: Inhibits insect, but not mammalian, voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like acurhagin
description: Snake venom zinc metalloprotease that causes hemorrhage and dose-dependently inhibits platelet aggregation triggered by collagen. This inhibition is due to its binding to glycoprotein VI (GP6) and collagen. The binding to GP6 results in inhibition of the signaling pathway (decrease of tyrosine phosphorylation of signaling proteins such as Syk, LAT, PI3-K and PLCgamma2). Preferentially cleaves alpha chain (FGA) of fibrinogen, followed by beta chain (FGB). Also degrades the extracellular matrix protein fibronectin (FN1), and cleaves collagen and von Willebrand factor (VWF).

name: Alpha-conotoxin VxXXIVA
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. The toxin with a disulfide connectivity C1-C2, C3-C4 (shown in the sequence annotation) block the rat nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (AChR) alpha-9-alpha-10/CHRNA9-CHRNA10 with an IC(50) of 1.2 uM, whereas the one with C1-C3, C2-C4 shows a lower activity with an IC(50) of 3.9 uM.

name: Tereporin-Ca1
description: Pore-forming protein that forms pores of around 1 nm and causes cardiac stimulation and hemolysis.

name: Tereporin-Ts1
description: Pore-forming protein that forms pores of around 1 nm and causes cardiac stimulation and hemolysis.

name: U1-cyrtautoxin-As1d
description: Is both paralytic and lethal, when injected into lepidopteran larvae.

name: U1-cyrtautoxin-As1c
description: Is both paralytic and lethal, when injected into lepidopteran larvae.

name: U3-cyrtautoxin-As1a
description: Is both paralytic and lethal, when injected into lepidopteran larvae. Is a slower acting toxin, being lethal at 24 hours, but not paralytic at 1 hour post-injection.

name: Potassium channel toxin alpha-KTx 15.9
description: Inhibits voltage-gated potassium channels.

name: Neurotoxin LmNaTx17
description: Binds voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing.

name: Neurotoxin LmNaTx10
description: Binds voltage-independently at site-3 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission.

name: Lipolysis-activating peptide 1-beta chain
description: The homodimer inhibits HMG-CoA reductase (HMGCR) (32% of inhibition produced by 0.6 uM), a glycoprotein involved in the control of cholesterol biosynthesis. The inhibitory effects of bumarsin are seen at much lower concentrations (0.6 uM) than that for statins such as atorvastatin (5 mM) and simvastatin (10 uM). In addition to inhibition of HMG-CoA reductase, this protein lowers cholesterol levels by inducing steroid hormone synthesis via StAR, and by increasing reverse cholesterol transport mediated by the induction of ABCA1 and APOA1 (By similarity).

name: Neurotoxin LmNaTx28
description: Binds voltage-independently at site-4 of sodium channels (Nav) and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing.

name: Lipolysis-activating peptide 1-alpha chain
description: The heterodimer non-edited LVP1 induces lipolysis in rat adipocytes. Induction of lipolysis by LVP1 appears to be mediated through the beta-2 adrenergic receptor pathway (ADRB2) (By similarity).

name: Neurotoxin alpha-KTx 29.1
description: Weakly inhibits the Kv1.3/KCNA3 channel (1 uM of thetoxin inhibits currents by 13.2%) and Kv7.1/KCNQ1 channel (10 uM of the toxin inhibits currents by 27.7%).

name: Tau-theraphotoxin-Hs1a
description: Selectively activates mammalian TRPV1, or capsaicin receptor, a nonselective cation channel expressed by sensory neurons of the pain pathway. Binds to TRPV1 in an open state-dependent manner, trapping it there to produce irreversible currents.

name: U21-theraphotoxin-Cg1a 2
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: Beta-mammal toxin CeII9
description: Beta toxins bind at site-4 of sodium channels and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing. This toxin is active against mammals and lethal to mice. Selectively modulates Nav1.4/SCN4A, a sodium channel present in both denervated and innervated skeletal muscle.

name: Beta-toxin CeII8
description: Beta toxins bind at site-4 of sodium channels and shift the voltage of activation toward more negative potentials thereby affecting sodium channel activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing. Has a selective effect toward Nav1.7/SCN9A which plays a role in pain mechanisms, and especially in the development of inflammatory pain. Shows no lethality toward mice.

name: U21-theraphotoxin-Cg1c
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U21-theraphotoxin-Cg1b
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U2-theraphotoxin-Cg1b 2
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U2-theraphotoxin-Cg1b 1
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U23-theraphotoxin-Cg1a 1
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: U22-theraphotoxin-Cg1a
description: Probable ion channel inhibitor.

name: Antimicrobial peptide scolopin-2
description: Antimicrobial peptide against both Gram-positive, -negative and yeast. Also induces histamine release by mast cells and shows moderate hemolytic activities against both human and rabbit red cells.

name: Antimicrobial peptide scolopin-1
description: Antimicrobial peptide against both Gram-positive, -negative and yeast. Also induces histamine release by mast cells and shows moderate hemolytic activities against both human and rabbit red cells.

name: Cytotoxin 1
description: Shows cytolytic activity on many different cells by forming pore in lipid membranes. In vivo, increases heart rate or kills the animal by cardiac arrest. In addition, it binds to heparin with high affinity, interacts with Kv channel-interacting protein 1 (KCNIP1) in a calcium-independent manner, and binds to integrin alpha-V/beta-3 (ITGAV/ITGB3) with moderate affinity.

name: Cytotoxin 3
description: Monomer: shows cytolytic activity.

name: M-zodatoxin-Lt8k
description: Insecticidal, cytolytic and antimicrobial peptide. Forms voltage-dependent, ion-permeable channels in membranes. At high concentration causes cell membrane lysis (By similarity).

name: M-zodatoxin-Lt8l
description: Insecticidal, cytolytic and antimicrobial peptide. Forms voltage-dependent, ion-permeable channels in membranes. At high concentration causes cell membrane lysis (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1aiii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1aiv
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: M-zodatoxin-Lt8m
description: Insecticidal, cytolytic and antimicrobial peptide. Forms voltage-dependent, ion-permeable channels in membranes. At high concentration causes cell membrane lysis (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1bii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1biii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SpaSicTox-betaIIA3
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: M-zodatoxin-Lt8o
description: Insecticidal, cytolytic and antimicrobial peptide. Forms voltage-dependent, ion-permeable channels in membranes. At high concentration causes cell membrane lysis (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1ai
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1aii
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1biv
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D SdSicTox-betaIIB1bv
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Does not cause hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation (By similarity).

name: Phospholipase D LiSicTox-betaID1
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin with a low activity. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Causes dermonecrosis, induces inflammatory response, platelet aggregation and increases vessel permeability. Shows no lethality when injected at higher dose into mice. Is less active than LiRecDT4 in phospholipase activity and platelet aggregation. May cause complement-dependent hemolysis. In addition, may also induce hemolysis in a complement-dependent manner and probably also in a complement-independent manner. The hemolysis provoked in a complement-independent manner may be composed of several steps. The toxin may bind to erythrocyte membranes, may hydrolyze membrane phospholipids (sphingomyelin and lysophosphatidylcholine) thus generating metabolism products that may cause hemolysis, probably by provoking an increase of calcium inside cells. The calcium influx may be due to the opening of L-type calcium channels, since L-type calcium channel blockers inhibit calcium influx.

name: Phospholipase D LiSicTox-alphaII1
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin. May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. Shows high hemolytic and catalytic activities. Causes dermonecrosis, induces inflammatory response, platelet aggregation and increases vessel permeability. Shows no lethality when injected at higher dose into mice. May cause complement-dependent hemolysis as well as in a complement-independent manner (PubMed:21590705). The hemolysis provoked in a complement-independent manner may be composed of several steps. The toxin may bind to erythrocyte membranes, may hydrolyze membrane phospholipids (sphingomyelin and lysophosphatidylcholine) thus generating metabolism products that may cause hemolysis, probably by provoking an increase of calcium inside cells. The calcium influx may be due to the opening of L-type calcium channels, since L-type calcium channel blockers inhibit calcium influx.

name: Snake venom vascular endothelial growth factor toxin
description: Induces capillary permeability and angiogenesis through VEGF receptor (KDR/VEGFR-2) signaling.

name: Alpha-conotoxin EIVA
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. This toxin binds with high affinity to both fetal (alpha-1/beta-1/epsilon/delta subunits) and adult (alpha-1/beta-1/gamma/delta subunits) mammalian muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR).

name: Alpha-conotoxin EIVB
description: Alpha-conotoxins act on postsynaptic membranes, they bind to the nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) and thus inhibit them. This toxin binds with high affinity to both fetal (alpha-1/beta-1/epsilon/delta subunits) and adult (alpha-1/beta-1/gamma/delta subunits) mammalian muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR).

name: Alpha-latrotoxin associated low molecular weight protein 2
description: May increase the toxicity of alpha-latrotoxin and/or other venom components. Is non-toxic to mice and to the cockroach Periplaneta americana.

name: Beta-hexatoxin-Mr1a
description: Insect and vertebrate active toxin. Binds at site 4 of mammalian voltage-gated sodium channels and shifts the activation voltage of the mammalian rNav1.2a (SCN2A) channel to more hyperpolarized voltages, whereas the insect channel, DmNav1 (para), is not affected. Causes temporary paralysis when injected into lepidopteran larvae at 8.6 nmol/g. A low intracranial injection dose into mice causes lacrimation, closure of the eyes and sweating. A high injection dose causes extensive lacrimation and death.

name: U5-hexatoxin-Mr1a
description: This toxin blocks the neuromuscular transmission, and also acts on muscle. It exerts an effect of first exciting and then inhibiting the contraction of muscle. This toxin is active only against mammals.

name: U9-barytoxin-Tl1a
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: U13-barytoxin-Tl1a
description: Ion channel inhibitor.

name: Alpha-latrotoxin associated low molecular weight protein
description: May increase the toxicity of alpha-latrotoxin and/or other venom components. Is non-toxic to mice and to the cockroach Periplaneta americana.

name: Alpha-D-conotoxin GeXXA
description: Alpha-D-conopeptides act as non-competitive inhibitors of nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR). This toxin has strong inhibitory activity on rat alpha-9-alpha-10 (CHRNA9/CHRNA10) (IC(50)=1.2 nM) and a moderate inhibitory activity on human alpha-7 (CHRNA7) (IC(50)=210 nM), rat alpha-3-beta-2 (CHRNA3/CHRNB2) (IC(50)=498 nM), rat alpha-3-beta-4 (CHRNA3/CHRNB4) (IC(50)=614 nM) and rat alpha-1-beta-1-delta-epsilon (CHRNA1/CHRNB1/CHRNE/CHRND) (IC(50)=743 nM) subtypes. Shows a weaker inhibitory activity on human alpha-9-alpha-10 (IC(50)=28 nM) than on the rat channel. This is explained by a different residue in the probable binding site (His-31 in rat alpha-10 and Leu-31 in human).

name: Delta-conotoxin-like MVID
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Delta-conotoxin-like MVIB
description: Delta-conotoxins bind to site 6 of voltage-gated sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation process.

name: Venom metalloproteinase 1
description: The recombinant protein has gelatinase activity. In vivo, injection of this recombinant into fifth instar L.oleracea (host) larvae results in partial insect mortality associated with the molt to sixth instar, with surviving insects showing retarded development and growth (By similarity).

name: Venom metalloproteinase 2
description: The recombinant protein has gelatinase activity. In vivo, injection of this recombinant into fifth instar L.oleracea (host) larvae results in partial insect mortality associated with the molt to sixth instar, with surviving insects showing retarded development and growth (By similarity).

name: Venom metalloproteinase 3
description: The recombinant protein has gelatinase activity. In vivo, injection of this recombinant into fifth instar L.oleracea (host) larvae results in partial insect mortality associated with the molt to sixth instar, with surviving insects showing retarded development and growth.

name: Toxin Acra III-1
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and affects the channel activation process.

name: Toxin Acra III-2
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and affects the channel activation process.

name: Toxin Acra II-2
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and affects the channel activation process.

name: Toxin Acra II-3
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and affects the channel activation process.

name: Toxin Acra I-3
description: Probable neurotoxin that inhibits ion channels (By similarity). Is toxic to mice.

name: Toxin Acra II-1
description: Binds to sodium channels (Nav) and affects the channel activation process.

name: Astacin-like metalloprotease toxin 3
description: Zinc metalloprotease. Provoques deadhesion of endothelial cells from cell cultures, and also degradation of fibronectin, fibrinogen and gelatin in vitro. Its role in the venom is not fully understood but it might act as a spreading factor that facilitates diffusion of other venom toxins. Alternatively, it might be involved in the proteolytic processing of other venom toxins or it might play a role in extra-oral digestion of prey (By similarity).

name: Toxin Acra I-2
description: Probable neurotoxin that inhibits ion channels (By similarity). Is toxic to mice. Is about 2.8% of the total protein in the venom.

name: Phospholipase D LbSicTox-betaIA1a
description: Does not have sphingomyelinase and dermonecrotic activities.

name: Phospholipase D LbSicTox-alphaIB1a
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin (about 31.5 U/mg). May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. May induce complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation.

name: Phospholipase D LrSicTox-alphaIB1
description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of sphingomyelin (18.3 U/mg). May also act on other phosphatidyl esters. May induce complement-dependent hemolysis, dermonecrosis, blood vessel permeability and platelet aggregation.

name: Chi-conotoxin MrIB
description: Chi-conotoxins inhibit the neuronal noradrenaline transporter (NET/SLC6A2).

name: Rho-conotoxin TIA
description: Allosteric inhibitor of alpha-1B adrenergic receptors (ADRA1B). Binds to an allosteric modulatory site on transmembrane helix 6 and 7 at the base of extracellular loop 3 of ADRA1B (PubMed:23184947). Also weekly inhibits alpha-1A (ADRA1A) and alpha-1D (ADRA1D) adrenergic receptors in a competive manner (PubMed:15194691). Potently inhibits contractions of vas deferens, spleen and aorta in response to noradrenaline (PubMed:15680270).

name: Muscarinic toxin Mlalpha
description: Probably blocks muscarinic acetylcholine receptors (CHRM), since it inhibits the binding of the selective muscarinic ligand [3H]QNB and inhibits the carbachol-induced [3H]inositol phosphate accumulation in rat hippocampus.

name: Snaclec bothroinsularin subunit alpha
description: Thrombin and prothrombin (F2) inhibitor. The IC(50) of thrombin-induced platelet aggregation and fibrinocoagulation is 62 and 35 nM, respectively. Its inhibitory activity is at least 10-fold lower than that observed for other thrombin inhibitors.

name: Short neurotoxin 2
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Phospholipase A2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Phospholipase A2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Short neurotoxin 1
description: Binds to muscle nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibit acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular transmission.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin stejnitin
description: Snake venom zinc metalloproteinase that inhibits ADP-induced platelet aggregation in human platelet-rich plasma (IC(50) is 175 nM) and cleaves alpha-(FGA) and subsequently the beta-chain (FGG) of bovine fibrinogen, leaving the gamma-chain unaffected. It is also able to inhibit proliferatin of ECV304 cells by inducing apoptosis of these cells.

name: Alpha-like toxin Bom4
description: Binds voltage-independently sodium channels (Nav) and inhibits the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. This alpha-like toxin is highly toxic to mice and insects.

name: Alpha-mammal toxin Lqh2
description: Alpha toxins bind voltage-independently at site-3 of sodium channels (Nav) and inhibit the inactivation of the activated channels, thereby blocking neuronal transmission. The dissociation is voltage-dependent. Is active on mammals and competes for alpha-toxins binding on both mammalian and cockroach sodium channels.

name: Disintegrin EC6 subunit beta
description: Potently inhibits adhesion of alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) and alpha-9/beta-1 (ITGA9/ITGB1) integrins to VCAM1, and adhesion of alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) integrin to fibronectin. Has a much less effect on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) integrin. Also potently inhibits neutrophil migration across TNF-alpha-activated human umbilical endothelial cells.

name: Muscarinic toxin-like protein 3
description: Antagonist of muscle and neuronal nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) with highest affinity for neuronal alpha-7 nAChRs.

name: Disintegrin EC6 subunit alpha
description: Potently inhibits adhesion of alpha-4/beta-1 (ITGA4/ITGB1) and alpha-9/beta-1 (ITGA9/ITGB1) integrins to VCAM1, and adhesion of alpha-5/beta-1 (ITGA5/ITGB1) integrin to fibronectin. Has a much less effect on alpha-IIb/beta-3 (ITGA2B/ITGB3) integrin. Also potently inhibits neutrophil migration across TNF-alpha-activated human umbilical endothelial cells.

name: Muscarinic toxin-like protein 1
description: Binds weakly to the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor (CHRM).

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like brevilysin H2a
description: Non-hemorrhagic metalloproteinase that degrades fibrinogen. The alpha chain (FGA) is rapidly degraded, the beta chain (FGB) is degraded very slowly, while the gamma chain is left intact.

name: Zinc metalloproteinase-disintegrin-like jerdohagin
description: Snake venom metalloproteinase that has high hemorrhagic activity and degrades the alpha-chain of fibrinogen (FGA), leaving the beta- and the gamma-chain intact. It may also inhibit platelet aggregation.

name: Kunitz-type U15-theraphotoxin-Hs1d
description: Dual-function toxin that inhibits both serine proteases and voltage-gated potassium channels (Kv).

name: Weak toxin CM-9a
description: Binds with low affinity to muscular (alpha-1-beta-1-epsilon-delta/CHRNA1-CHRNB1-CHRNE-CHRND) and very low affinity to neuronal (alpha7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Long neurotoxin 1
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Long neurotoxin 1
description: Binds with high affinity to muscular (alpha-1/CHRNA1) and neuronal (alpha-7/CHRNA7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) and inhibits acetylcholine from binding to the receptor, thereby impairing neuromuscular and neuronal transmission.

name: Weak toxin 3
description: Binds with low affinity to muscular (alpha-1-beta-1-epsilon-delta/CHRNA1-CHRNB1-CHRNE-CHRND) and very low affinity to neuronal (alpha7) nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR).

name: Basic phospholipase A2 beta-bungarotoxin A1 chain
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows presynaptic neurotoxicity. The A chain has phospholipase activity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor A
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor B
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor C
description: Serine protease inhibitor.

name: Basic phospholipase A2 beta-bungarotoxin A2 chain
description: Snake venom phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that shows presynaptic neurotoxicity. PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides (By similarity).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor homolog beta-bungarotoxin B1 chain
description: Beta-bungarotoxin is a presynaptic neurotoxin of the venom. The B chain is homologous to venom basic protease inhibitors but has no protease inhibitor activity and is non-toxic (By similarity).

name: Kunitz-type serine protease inhibitor homolog beta-bungarotoxin B2a chain
description: Beta-bungarotoxin is a presynaptic neurotoxin of the venom. The B chain is homologous to venom basic protease inhibitors but has no protease inhibitor activity and is non-toxic (By similarity).

name: Snaclec echicetin subunit alpha
description: Binding of echicetin to GPIbalpha (GP1BA) receptor on platelets alone results in inhibition of platelet aggregation, while binding to both GP1BA receptor and IgMk promotes platelet aggregation and signal transduction.

name: Acidic phospholipase A2
description: PLA2 catalyzes the calcium-dependent hydrolysis of the 2-acyl groups in 3-sn-phosphoglycerides.

name: Cysteine-rich venom protein triflin
description: Blocks contraction of smooth muscle elicited by high potassium-induced depolarization (PubMed:12047379). May target voltage-gated calcium channels (Cav) on smooth muscle.

name: Snaclec echicetin subunit beta
